title: apple cake
directions: Sift Fine Spun flour and other dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and other ingredients together and add to the dry, small amounts at a time.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs, mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter and oil in large skillet.
Saute beef in batches over high heat, browning thoroughly.
Add more butter and oil if necessary.
Add salt, paprika, pepper, Kitchen Bouquet, broth and ketchup.
Simmer until meat is tender (about 20 minutes).
Combine flour and water; add to meat mixture; stir until thick.
In a separate skillet melt butter and oil.
Saute onions, garlic and mushrooms until brown (about 20 minutes over high heat).
Add vegetables to meat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and serve over rice or noodles.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: six dozen bran muffins
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Combine boiling water with baking soda; mix and let cool.
Add eggs.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour, Bran Flakes and All-Bran.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender and drain.
Mash until smooth.
Add other ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Place in microwave.
Heat through and through.
No grease necessary except when using electric oven, then put in greased dish and heat at 350° until warm. This will stay good in refrigerator about a week.

title: pillsbury nut quick bread mix
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes; loosen edges.

title: light and easy chili
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer awhile.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions.
Drain well.
Add celery soup and Cheddar cheese. Sprinkle almonds over top and bake 20 to 25 minutes in 375° oven.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Put eggs in double boiler, add vinegar and sugar.
Boil and stir constantly until smooth.
Lower heat and add butter, cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, salt, milk and 3/4 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Uncover and cook without stirring until a little ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until thickened and loses its gloss.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne; drain and rinse.
Brown hamburger; drain and crumble.
Grate cheeses, putting each in a separate bowl.
In a large baking dish, start with lasagne, layering each item (lasagne, meat, cheeses and sauce), finishing with a layer of lasagne and remainder of Prego sauce.
Top with sharp cheese. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Can be heated through in the microwave and is done when cheese topping melts.

title: butterscotch crunch drops
directions: You will also need wax paper and cookie sheet.

title: broken glass torte
directions: Mix Jell-O with water and congeal in separate containers.
Mix gelatin in cold water and add 1 cup hot pineapple juice; set aside to cool.
Whip cream (or use Cool Whip) until stiff and add sugar and vanilla.
Add cooled gelatin and pineapple juice to whipped cream.
Cut congealed Jell-O into small cubes and gently fold into whipped cream mixture.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Make pastry for 1 crust pie.
Line 9-inch pie pan.
Build up high and fluted edge.
Beat eggs slightly, then beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake just until knife inserted 1 inch from side of filling comes out clean at 425° (25 to 30 minutes).
Too long baking makes custard watery.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: To make meatballs, combine all the ingredients.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Put enough oil in pan to brown the meatballs. Add the sauce and simmer on low heat for 1 hour. These freeze real well and makes 80 or more meatballs.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together sugar, margarine and egg.
Add vanilla and pineapple with juice.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Combine brown sugar and coconut.
Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with ice cream.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix and put on stove the peach jello, flour and crushed pineapple.
Bring to a good boil.
Then cool.

title: angel popovers
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat until well blended.
Grease muffin pans and fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: white chocolate crunch
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water in a double boiler.
Crush pretzels and Spanish peanuts until they are large crumbs.
Fold into the melted chocolate.
Spread mixture into a thin layer on a cookie sheet which has been lined with waxed paper.
Cool until set, about 1 hour, and break into bite size pieces.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Vigorously mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Line muffin tins with cupcake liners.
Spoon ingredients into liners.
Freeze fruit salad until frozen.
Yield: Approximately 2 dozen.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all together and fry until brown.

title: the infamous cargo
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender container.
Blend and pour into a chilled goblet.
Serves 1.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix together in separate bowl the flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Pour in Bundt pan and cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in softened margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; stir well.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in half package of chocolate chips.
Pour batter into greased pan.
Sprinkle with remaining chips and the nutmeats (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: gooey cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Put in greased cake pan.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in small amount of water until tender.
Season with salt, pepper, bacon grease and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Most of the liquid should be cooked out.
Combine vegetables, celery, bell pepper, onion, mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix well. Spoon into 2-quart greased casserole dish. Cook at 300° until heated through and through and bubbly.
Remove from oven. Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Return to oven and cook until brown.

title: jalapeno pepper corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in iron skillet at 400 degrees.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Put rhubarb in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle sugar over rhubarb. Sprinkle Jell-O over sugar.
Put marshmallows over top of Jell-O. Make cake as directed on package.
Put over marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Brown meat and onion and drain well.
Saute zucchini and green pepper in oleo for 5 minutes and drain.
Layer crescent rolls in pie pan, then meat and onion, half the cheeses, zucchini and pepper.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°; add remaining cheeses and put back in oven for 15 minutes.

title: deanie's pie crust
directions: Cut shortening, flour and salt together real well.
Mix eggs, vinegar and water together real well.
Add to flour mixture, mix well.
It will be sticky.
Can be put in refrigerator.
Bring out and let get to room temperature.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; boil until soft.
Pour water off, then mash.
Add 2 tablespoons butter, small amount of milk, salt and pepper to potatoes.
While potatoes are cooking, brown ground beef and onion.
Add Worcestershire, Heinz 57, salt and pepper.
Place meat in baking dish and cover with mashed potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Place in oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: farm style stew
directions: Sprinkle beef with salt, pepper, paprika and seasoned salt. Add hot water and cover; cook on low for 7 to 9 hours.
Add zucchini and corn; add cornstarch to the 3 tablespoons of cold water and dissolve.
Add steak sauce and cornstarch mixture to other ingredients.
Cook on high for 12 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: avocado jello salad
directions: Use 1/2 cup boiling water per pack of Jell-O.
Add sugar and lemon juice and some of the pineapple juice while hot.
Let the Jell-O mixture begin to congeal (do not let it set), then add the crushed drained pineapple, Cool Whip, avocado and nuts.
Keeps 3 or 4 days in refrigerator.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix and cook 1 hour in a preheated 325° oven.

title: chili tamale pie
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in shortening until vegetables are tender. Stir in chili soup, water, vinegar and

Worcestershire sauce. Heat. Prepare cornbread mix as directed on package. Spread chili mixture evenly in a greased baking dish (10 x 6 x 2 1/2-inch). Spread batter over chili mixture. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zenith turtle sheet cake
directions: Unwrap caramels (around 36 perhaps) and place in saucepan with 2 tablespoons evaporated milk.
Set aside.

title: orange pralines
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in saucepan and boil until soft ball stage is reached (or slightly longer).
Let cool while you grate orange peel. Stir in orange peel and allow to cool until it begins to thicken somewhat.
Add pecans.
Spoon out onto greased wax paper and allow to cool.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix and roll out on floured board.
Cut to desired size with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 475° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: green bean casserole with meatballs
directions: Arrange meatballs in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper, French-fried onions and pimentos.
Blend gently.
Pour over meatballs in casserole. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: festive cake
directions: Butter and grease 9 x 13 inch pan.
In bowl, prepare cake mix according to directions.
Put in pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Meanwhile, in bowl, combine Jell-O and boiling water. Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Upon removing cake from oven, poke holes over entire cake.
Pour Jell-O over warm cake; set aside. In another bowl, prepare pudding.
When cake is cool, spread with pudding, then Cool Whip.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Microwave 8 minutes on High.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave one minute longer on High.
Add baking soda; quickly stir until light and foamy.
Immediately pour onto lightly buttered baking sheet.
Spread out thin.
When cooled, break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sugar-free punch
directions: Mix all together. Chill in freezer until mushy is best.
Makes 1 gallon or more.

title: red and white cabbage salad
directions: Combine the cabbages, carrots, onions and celery together in a mixing bowl.
Set aside and prepare miracle whip mixture by mixing miracle whip, vinegar, sugar, water and salt and pepper. Gently fold the mixture into the cabbage bowl.
Keep in cold place for 2 to 3 hours and then serve.

title: nacho dip
directions: Put hamburger, onion and green pepper in skillet; brown then drain.
Add taco seasonings and tomato paste.
Bring to boil.
Add can of refried beans; mix together.
Pour into baking pan.
Put sour cream on and then the cheese.
Sprinkle chili powder over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sausage-n-cheese casserole
directions: Place 6 slices of bread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and cayenne pepper.
Blend well and pour over bread slices.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: peanut brittle
directions: You will also need a candy thermometer.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Grease a 9x13 inch pan.
Arrange yams in the pan.
In skillet over medium heat, bring to a boil orange juice, Karo syrup, brown sugar and margarine.
Stir frequently.
Boil for 10 minutes or until thick and syrupy.
Pour over yams.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: krispy sherbet
directions: In a bowl, combine the butter, cereal and brown sugar until crumbly; set aside 3/4 cup for topping. Press remaining crumb mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: french bread
directions: In a large bowl mix the first 4 ingredients and about 3 cups of
flour
to
make
a
thin
batter ("sponge").
Mix the remainder of
the
flour
with batter and let rise 15 minutes. Knead for
minutes
and
place
in a greased pan.
Let rise another 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: tangy baked chicken
directions: Combine red and black pepper.
Rub on chicken breasts. Combine other ingredients; set aside about 1/2 of mixture.
Brush chicken breasts with other half.
Bake in a baking dish sprayed with Pam for about 25 minutes.
Serve remaining mixture, heated, with chicken.

title: russian sirniki(cheese pancake)
directions: In a bowl, mash the sour cream and the cream cheese until it is smooth.
Add the egg yolks, sugar and salt; mix well.
Add the cottage cheese and mix until smooth.
Sift the flour and add to previous mixture until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Heat 2 tablespoons of butter in saute pan and drop batter into pan.
Brown pancakes on both sides.
Serve with sour cream.

title: aunt wanda's oatmeal cookies deluxe
directions: Mix ingredients in order given. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet or pan covered with aluminum foil.
Bake at 365° for 8 minutes.

title: spaghetti tomato sauce
directions: Heat pan, add oil and lightly brown onion and green pepper. After they have started to cook, add the garlic and meat.
When light brown, add spices.
Mix well and add the tomato paste, cooking until mixture sticks to the pan; keep mixing.
Add 2 cans of water (12 ounces) to paste mixture and blend well.
Add chopped tomato mix and heat thoroughly.
Lower heat to a simmer and cook 3 to 4 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Cool.
Crumble 1/2; drop into punch bowl.
Mix vanilla pudding as instructed.
Let set up. Then put 1/2 over the cake pieces.
Put 1/2 cherry pie filling over pudding, then 1/2 pineapple over cherry pie filling.
Then slice 1/2 bananas over the pineapple and add 1/2 Cool Whip.
Start all over, repeating each step, finishing with Cool Whip and adding nuts on top.
Let set overnight to make moist.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas, one at a time.
Combine margarine and sugar. Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; add flour with bananas.
Stir in nuts. Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Boil crushed pineapple, cornstarch and sugar until clear.
Add orange jello.
Cool and add sliced banana, sour cherries and mandarin oranges.
Pour into pie crusts.
Refrigerate overnight or freeze.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: ham and cheese appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into rectangles about 2 x 1 1/2-inches. Serve warm (keep warm by placing on a warming tray).
Makes approximately 36.

title: herb roasted orange salmon
directions: Mix together the orange juice, olive oil, orange zest, garlic, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Add salmon and let set 1 hour, turning over every 10 to 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 475°.
Place salmon, skin side down, on baking sheet.
Pour marinade over top.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until salmon is just cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.

title: apple cake
directions: Bake in an angel food cake pan.
Do not grease pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Let cool in the pan.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix together the flour, salt and Crisco with pastry blender. Put the egg in a cup and finish filling cup with milk.
Blend well.
Add the vinegar.
Add the liquid to dry ingredients.
Mix with spoon.
Yields 3 double pie crusts.

title: hot olive cheese puffs appetizers
directions: Blend cheese with melted oleo.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika-blend.
Wrap 1 teaspoon dough around each olive.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: apricot salad
directions: Pour pear juice over Jell-O and bring to a boil.
Beat cream cheese into hot Jell-O.
When dissolved, add pears, Cool Whip and nuts.
Congeal.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Boil potato in skin until well done.
Take peeling off and mash well.
Mix powdered sugar with potato until it is thick enough to roll out.
(It takes about 1 pound box.)

title: squash supreme
directions: Cut up zucchini, summer squash and onions.
Add spices and cheese.
Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: white toffee cookies
directions: Cream together butter, margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill or drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° until very lightly browned.

title: sloppy joe lasagna
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Add Manwich sauce and chopped onion.
Heat thoroughly.
Let refrigerate 1 or 2 hours, if time allows.
To hamburger mixture, add spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, sugar, oregano, basil, pepper and garlic.
Stir over medium heat until hot.
Boil lasagna noodles for 5 minutes and drain.
Layer noodles in bottom of baking dish, layer sauce mixture, layer Mozzarella cheese and repeat layering and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook milk and sugar until a soft ball forms.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Spread on wax paper in a pan and refrigerate until it sets.
Cut in small squares.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Coat chicken breasts in bread crumbs; brown chicken lightly. Remove chicken; put in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top chicken with 1 slice each of ham and cheese.
To chicken drippings, add butter (melted) and flour; make a roux.
Add chicken broth, heavy cream and wine.
Return to heat, stirring until thick.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be prepared ahead of time.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add chili powder. Spread cream cheese in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish, then add browned hamburger. Cover with salsa and top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with dipping chips.

title: famous fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and salt.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallows, chocolate morsels, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until blended well. Pour into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: overnight brunch
directions: Arrange bread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese over bread.
Cover with meat or mushrooms (or combination). Mix eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over all.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine butter and sugar. Add eggs.
Mix together.
Mix all dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients together. Chill dough.
Roll out and shape.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: mexican 5 layer dip
directions: In a baking dish (at least 2-inches deep), layer the cream cheese, olives, chiles and chili, then top with the grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes (until bubbly).

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Sausage and cheese need to be at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients by hand.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 100 balls.

title: crabmeat coquille
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in saucepan.
Add onions.
Cover and cook 3 minutes over low heat.
Add crabmeat and mushrooms.
Season to taste.
Cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add fish stock.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Then remove crabmeat and mushrooms and set aside. Reserve cooking liquid.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into thin strips and brown in Dutch oven in small amount of oil and margarine.
Add beef broth, onion, celery, salt, garlic and ginger; simmer, covered, for 35 to 40 minutes, or until tender.
Add green peppers, mushrooms and tomatoes; cook an additional 10 minutes.
Mix soy sauce and cornstarch in 1 cup water until smooth.
Slowly stir into sauce and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape in pan and cover with catsup. Bake at 350° until well done.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: In medium saucepan, boil butter, cocoa and milk for 30 seconds.
Remove from heat and add almost the whole box of powdered sugar and vanilla; mix.
If too thick, add warm milk.

title: easy chuck roast
directions: Pour enough A-1 sauce over meat to lightly cover it. Sprinkle dry soup mix over meat and add can of soup. Put in heavy duty foil and wrap tightly on all ends and sides. Bake in an open roaster at 350 degrees for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: party punch
directions: Bring
4 cups water and sugar to boil, then add Jell-O. Add other
ingredients,
except
Sprite
or
ginger
ale, and freeze. Makes 2 to 3 gallons.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Mix thoroughly in order of list for best results.
Chill until firm.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Boil carrots in water until tender; drain.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat; add honey and lemon juice, stirring until smooth.
Add carrots, tossing gently.
Serve.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and roll out on a biscuit sheet until stiff; cut in four parts.
Press into 8-inch cake pan.
Makes four thin layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread applesauce between each layer.

title: crunchy banana cake
directions: In bowl, mix pecans,
coconut, brown sugar, oatmeal and butter.
Set aside.
With
mixer,
combine
sour
cream, eggs, banana and dry
cake mix.
In well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan, place half of cake batter, then half of nut mixture. Repeat layers.
Bake
in preheated 350° oven until done, about 1 hour.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: In a big bowl, mix wafers, sugar, eggs, milk and butter.
Mix very well.
Add in coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and chives.
Spread thinly on each slice of bread.
Roll tightly, then wrap with bacon securing with a toothpick.
Place on broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, turning if necessary.

title: corn chowder
directions: Chop bacon into small pieces and chop onion. Saute together until lightly brown. Drain potatoes. Add corn and creamed corn to bacon and onion. You can add milk and/or water to create density you want and simmer, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate torte
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and walnuts together like a pie crust.
Spread on bottom of spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Combine cake mix and oats.
Stir in melted margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Put 3/4 cup mix in 9 x 13-inch pan; press evenly.
Combine jam and water and spread on.
Top with remaining mix.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Chop onions in food processor.
Open and empty cans of tomatoes and beans in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Add onion to tomatoes, beans and add raw ground beef.
Mix well.
Cook, uncovered, over medium-low heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This soup will be thick and can be eaten as a dip with heavier chips such as Doritos or Fritos.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Heat milk to 110° to 115°, remove from heat.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm milk in a small bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes. Combine remaining milk, honey, shortening, salt and whole wheat flour; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth. Add yeast and eggs; mix well.
Gradually stir in enough all-purpose flour to make a stiff dough.
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: tea punch
directions: Let tea and 4 cups boiling water stand for 5 minutes.
Boil 2 more quarts water and sugar for 1 minute.
When cold add orange juice, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Add this to tea and add 6 more quarts water.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine bananas, oil, honey, eggs and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Coat a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan with cooking spray.
Spoon batter into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mom's jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let set at room temperature for 8 hours.
Cook at 110° for 8 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Pour oil in bowl.
Sift flour, sugar, spice and salt together. Add 1/2 part of this and 1 egg at a time until all is used.
Add nuts and carrots.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° in tube pan.

title: kolohe's banana pancakes
directions: Make pancake batter according to any pancake mix.
Add sliced bananas.
You can add as many or as little as you like as long as the batter covers the banana slices.
Fry as normal.
These are great to eat plain when cooled, or may be frozen and used when desired.

title: layered orange salad
directions: Save juice from pineapple; use 1 cup of juice in 3rd layer. Add remaining juice to water to make 1 3/4 cups boiling liquid. Mix jello and liquid.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish.
Chill until jello begins to thicken; add pineapple.
Let congeal in refrigerator.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut shortening into mix.
Gradually add milk.
Work into a smooth dough.
Divide dough into 3 parts; roll to about 1/16-inch.
Whip or mash sausage until it spreads easily. Spread about 1/3 sausage over dough.
Roll like jelly roll.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Repeat with remaining dough and sausage.
Chill for 1 hour or overnight.
Slice 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fresh stuffed peppers
directions: Boil peppers in salt water for 5 minutes.
Drain and cool slightly.
Cook beef and onion until brown.
Mix all ingredients together and stuff peppers.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.
Serve with salad and garlic bread for a real good meal.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in the top of a double boiler. Heat and blend all ingredients together. When smooth and creamy, add crabmeat and sherry. Heat thoroughly.
Serve in chafing dish with king size Fritos.

title: basic chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish. Add spices. Mix bouillon with 1 c. hot water and pour into baking dish. Cook chicken in slow oven 325-350° for 1 hour. The bouillon will make the chicken very flavorful and tender. Don't have any bouquet garni? Add any spices you wish, just make sure the bouillon doesn't cover the chicken and wash away the spices.

title: pie crust for two crust pie
directions: Sift four and salt.
Cut in Crisco until coarse like corn meal. Sprinkle water and vinegar over until it holds pastry together.
It may not take 6 tablespoons of water.
Form into two balls.
Roll out to fit pie tin.
Put in filling and roll out the other ball to fit the top.
Cut air holes in top to let out steam.
Cut excess dough that hangs over pan.
Pinch both crusts together.
Wash the top with little milk.
Makes it brown nice and shiny.

title: sesame dressing
directions: Brown sesame seed in 200° oven, stirring occasionally. Combine next 5 ingredients in blender.
Add oil and vinegar slowly.
Pour into jar.
Add sesame seed and chill in refrigerator.
Great with green salad and pasta salad.

title: low calorie seafood okra gumbo
directions: Combine oysters and cold water.
Stir and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Strain and refrigerate oysters and oyster water until ready to use.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Reserve 1/2 cup.
Stir together remaining soup, rice, mushroom soup and 1/2 onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased baking dish, 11 x 7-inch.
Arrange chicken breasts on rice mixture.
Pour reserved soup mix over chicken and sprinkle with onion soup.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: meringue(makes enough for 1 pie)
directions: Use a glass or metal bowl.
Beat egg whites until you leave beater marks in the whites.
Add a dash of salt and continue to beat until peaks form when you pull the beaters out.
Add sugar while beating.
Ready to put on top of the pie.
Bake until brown.

title: simply sensational cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine crumbs, sugar and shortening.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: salmon spread
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Chill until firm. Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts (pecans or walnuts).
Serve with your favorite crackers.
Yields 2 cups.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend all ingredients, refrigerate overnight.
Can be served on toast or with bread.
My preference is to take a round loaf of pumpernickel bread (the color contrast looks nice) or any bread you prefer.
Hollow out the bread making a nice bowl, saving the bread you remove to place around the edges of the "bread bowl" to eat with the dip.

title: mexican canapes
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage and drain well.
Add Velveeta and remaining ingredients.
Cook together until cheese is melted. While mixture is warm, spread on flour tortillas or toast.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes, or until sausage is done.

title: fancy pretzels
directions: Put all ingredients into plastic bag for 1 hour shaking 3 or 4 times during that time. (You can pour onto paper toweling to absorb any extra oil.)

title: popovers
directions: Use 2 1/2 inch deep custard cups that are greased well.
Place on jelly roll pan for easy handling.

title: puppy chow
directions: Over medium heat, melt peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips.
Pour into cereal, a little at a time, stirring until all is coated.
Put sugar in a large plastic bag.
Pour mixture into bag and shake gently until all is coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: bonbons
directions: Melt chocolate and paraffin in a double boiler.
Mix other ingredients and shape into small balls.
Dip the balls in the chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Combine 1 package Country Herb dip mix with sour cream and chilies.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Just before serving, spread refried beans in bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Spoon dip mixture over beans and top with cheese, tomato and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.
You may add your own favorite ingredients.
Enjoy.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix milk, sour cream and tang together.
Fold in half of cool whip.
Spoon into the pie shell.
Top with remaining cool whip.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown meat and onion in 3 qt. saucepan. Drain off excess fat; add sauce, water, parsley, salt and pepper. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Mix Ricotta cheese with eggs and Parmesan cheese. Place 1 c. sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Layer 3 pieces of uncooked lasagne over sauce; cover with 1 1/2 c. sauce. Spread 1/2 of Ricotta cheese, then place 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers of lasagne, sauce and cheeses. Top with layer of lasagne and remaining sauce. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for for 55 to 60 minutes. Remove foil; bake 10 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes; add pieces of bacon and minced onion. Bring to a boil in water.
When potatoes are done in the middle, drain water off and leave in the pan.
Mix eggs and flour together until the mixture is not runny.
Add milk to potatoes and butter. Bring to a boil, then remove from burner.
Add flour and egg mixture.
Separate with a fork and cover with the lid.
Soup ready to serve in 1/2 hour.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine peaches, orange juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain juice and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Add 1 cup sugar and cornstarch to liquid.
Bring to boil until thick and clear.
Add almond flavoring and butter.
Let cool.
Stir in raw sliced peaches and pour into Graham Cracker Crust.
Refrigerate.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in casserole; use 3 tablespoons in corn mixture and leave remainder in casserole to brown edges of pudding.
Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly in bowl.
Pour into warm buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: cool and fruity pound cake
directions: Slice pound cake lengthwise 3 times.
Spread Cool Whip on first layer.
Next, layer about 3 pineapple slices on top of Cool Whip.
After that, put the bananas, strawberries or really any other fruit you want or even use 2 fruits if you want.
Repeat directions for the next 2 slices.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In a sifter place the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, ground cloves, allspice and pumpkin pie spice.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add applesauce, mixing thoroughly.
Put 3 tablespoons flour in nuts and raisin mix (this is so they won't sink in mixture).
Add flour-spice mix, blending until moist.
Do not overmix.
Place in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza sticks
directions: Separate and unroll bread sticks.
Place 3 pepperoni slices in single layer over one-half of each bread stick.
Fold remaining half of bread stick over top; seal end and twist.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Combine cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Sprinkle evenly over each bread stick.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with pizza sauce.
Makes 8 pizza sticks.

title: mozetti
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add 1 tablespoon water.
Add celery, onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: low-fat french toast
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together milk, egg white, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour into a large flat dish.
Dip both sides of bread lightly in milk mixture.
Coat a nonstick frying pan with nonstick spray.
Heat over medium-high heat; pour in oil.
Brown bread on both sides.
Serves 4.

title: rugalach
directions: Mix and roll above ingredients in four balls; refrigerate overnight.
Roll each ball into a pie shape.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each into 16 triangles.
Fill with fruit jam, nuts and raisins.
Grease sheet; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut lettuce and chop onion and green pepper.
Combine all ingredients, adding dressing last.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until cooked and debone into bite size pieces. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth until tender enough to cut through with a spoon.
Mix all ingredients and put into a casserole dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: wild rice with almonds
directions: Dip skinned chicken breasts in melted margarine.
Roll each in Ritz cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chewy coconut macaroons
directions: Grease and flour a large cookie sheet. Set aside. In a medium bowl, stir together coconut, sugar, flour and salt. Stir in egg whites and almond extract. Drop coconut mixture by rounded teaspoons 2-inches apart onto prepared cookie sheet. Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Transfer cookies to a wire rack and let cool.

title: super-easy vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth.
Chill.
Serve with your favorite vegetables.

title: mixed bean vinaigrette(heart healthy and low-fat)
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: seven-layer dip
directions: Layer in order listed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in boiling, salted water 5 to 8 minutes or until just tender; drain leaves.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl; add shortening and water and beat 1 minute.
Add applesauce and egg; beat 1 minute.
Add nuts and raisins. Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, dark corn syrup, eggs, salt, butter, vanilla and cocoa.
Add pecans.
Pour filling into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake for an additional 40 to 45 minutes or until filling doesn't wiggle.

title: white crunchies
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate morsels; set aside.
Combine cereal, raisins and nuts in a large container. Pour chocolate mixture over it; mix well.
Sift a box of powdered sugar into a large brown bag.
Pour the mixture in; shake until coated.

title: chicken and squirrel jambalaya
directions: Cut squirrel in pieces.
Boil until tender.
Debone.
Saute Chef's Blend in oil.
Add chicken drumettes and cook until tender, adding water to prevent burning.
In large pot mix squirrel, chicken mixture, Kitchen Bouquet and soy sauce and put on low heat. Rinse rice.
Add to meat and put water 1 inch over top.
Cover tightly and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook 30 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar and flour.
Beat egg whites; add to mixture.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake until brown at 325°, for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Add 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Put in pan.
Crush white saltines and spread over top.
Melt 1/2 cup oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Check occasionally.

title: french fried cauliflower
directions: Boil the cauliflower (head-up); drain and separate. Beat 2 egg yolks. Add 1/2 cup milk. Stir in 3/4 cup flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Beat the batter until it's smooth. Dip the cauliflower into the batter. Deep fry until golden brown.

title: cheesy apple crisp for a crowd(may double for about 40 servings)
directions: Arrange apples in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine water and lemon juice; sprinkle over apples.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Mix in cheese lightly and spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is crisp.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles in salted water until tender.
Mix tuna, soup, salt and pepper together in bowl.
Pour cooked noodles in large casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over noodles.
Cube cheese and mix with noodles.
Top with onions.
Bake in 400° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugars; add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients to mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake
at 400° until golden brown.

title: chunky chili
directions: In skillet, brown ground meat, onion, and peppers.
Stir in 1/2
pkg. of seasoning mix.

Salt and pepper to taste. (A couple shakes of Boone's Wild Island wine comes in great here!) In crock pot, combine kidney beans, diced tomatoes, tomato sauce, remaining seasoning mix, and 1/2 cup of water.
(You can splash some Texas Pete hot sauce in if you want to!) Add skillet mixture to crock-pot, stir it up.
Cook on low for 4 - 6 hours. Garnish with cheddar or mozzarella cheese.
Serve with cornbread and dig in!

title: effie drennan's french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream
margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at
a time, beating well with each addition.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in tube pan.

title: lime and horseradish salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the 1 1/4 cups water and allow to cool. Then add balance of ingredients and mix well.
Serves 6. Can be doubled.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make roux using oil and flour.
Add seasoning and cook until wilted.
Add tomato sauce, water and remaining ingredients.
Let simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Shape and pat out cookie dough in pizza pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar with flavored Cool Whip.
Top with sliced strawberries.

title: aunt mickey's punch bowl dessert
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on box.
Crumble cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Layer pineapple, vanilla pudding, cherry pie filling and Cool Whip.
Decorate with coconut, whole cherries and nuts.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: marisa's grilled minute steaks
directions: In a glass bowl or deep platter, combine oil, salt, pepper, garlic, parsley and either vinegar (any type) or juice from fresh lemon.
Whisk with a fork until blended; put aside.

title: meatless lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna according to directions. Saute onion, celery and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water and spices. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: ham noodle casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Drain noodles well.
Add butter and ham; toss lightly.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine broccoli, soup and milk; pour over noodles. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine 1/2 cup chicken broth, soy sauce, 1 teaspoon oil, garlic powder and ginger.
Mix well.
Add chicken and stir to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend well.
Makes almost a quart.

title: southern hot pot
directions: Saute the onions in hot oil until transparent.
Remove from heat; sprinkle with paprika and mix well.
Place cloves of garlic in the bottom of large ovenproof pot.
Add 1/3 of the vegetables (tomatoes, cabbage, carrot, peppers, cauliflower and parsnip).
On top of this, add half of the meat.
Add another layer of vegetables, the rest of the meat and the rest of the vegetables, flavoring each layer with salt and pepper.
Put onions on top and sprinkle on vinegar.

title: cranberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Chill until thickened, but not firm.
Break up cranberry sauce.
Stir into jello.
Add nuts. Fold in sour cream.
Chill.

title: fresh fruit pizza dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk, sour cream, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Chill.
In a large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in flour, oats and walnuts until blended.
On a lightly oiled pizza pan or baking sheet, press dough into 12-inch circle forming rim around edges.
Prick with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.
Spread filling evenly onto crust.
Arrange fruit on top of filling.
Chill before serving.

title: strawberry tapioca
directions: Heat water; add sugar and salt.
Bring to boil and add tapioca and simmer about 5 to 10 minutes until tapioca is clear. Immediately add jello.
Frozen strawberries can be put in while hot to melt.
Cool before adding fresh strawberries.
This is also good to use with fresh peaches and peach jello.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk, lime juice and food coloring.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 40 minutes.
Cool.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate.

title: six-week muffins
directions: In a pot, place brown sugar, water, raisins, margarine and spices.
On stove top, bring to boil and let cool.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and fork comes out clean.

title: doe's texas hash
directions: Cook ground beef, onions and peppers in cooking oil.
Cook until meat crumbles.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a simmer, then add 2 1/2 to 3 cups small egg noodles (uncooked). Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix and chill for veggies or crackers.

title: quick cherry delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill at least 1 hour.

title: mother murphey's potato soup
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in chunks.
Put potatoes and onion in large kettle.
Add pinch of salt.
Add enough water to cover and boil.
Cook until done.
Mash with potato masher into small chunks. Add cream or milk.
Thicken if desired.
(Mother thickened with flour, but today you could use instant potatoes.)
Add chopped hard boiled eggs.
May add cubed ham, cut up wieners or crisp bacon. MMMMMMM-Good!!!

title: all-american brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt the 1/2 pound butter and let cool.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and vanilla until foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar until blended and then beat in butter.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake until brownies begin to pull away from the sides of the pan, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool before cutting into squares.
Per brownie:
205 calories.

title: rocky mountain fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt chips in the sweetened condensed milk. Take off the stove. Stir in vanilla, marshmallows and nuts. Cut before it gets too hard.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate broccoli, onion, bacon, sunflower seeds and raisins.
Refrigerate several hours.
Stir together vinegar, mayonnaise and sugar and add to other ingredients before serving. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan. Mix sugar and butter in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in eggs until blended.
Add bananas and water. Beat 30 seconds.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except nuts, just until
moistened.
Stir in nuts. Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan. Remove. Cool before slicing. Yields 1 loaf, 24 slices.
Has 120 calories.

title: leftover sandwiches
directions: Toast bread.
Spoon leftover vegetables on top of toast.
Put one slice of cheese on top of vegetables. Place on cookie sheet and bake in oven at 350° until cheese is melted. (Leftover stir-fried vegetables are the best.)

title: layered crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in pie dish.

title: easy roast chicken and almonds
directions: Remove the necks and backbones from the chicken parts and reserve for another use.
Season chickens with salt and pepper. Lay in a shallow baking dish.
Cover with 2/3 of the almonds.
Mix the 3 cans of soup together with the wine.
Pour over the chicken and almonds.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and remainder of almonds over top.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: snow cone syrup
directions: Bring sugar and water to a full boil.
Remove from heat and stir in Kool-Aid.
Chill.
It's now ready for crushed ice.

title: potato logs
directions: Wash potatoes; do not peel.
Cut each potato into fourths. Soak in ice water for about 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to flour.
Batter each piece of potato in flour.
Drop battered potatoes into hot Crisco oil; fry on medium heat until tender.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan.
Bake until light brown. When cool, mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled cookie dough.
Add what fruit you like on top: strawberries, grapes, melons, kiwi, etc.

title: carol's cinnamon cider
directions: Place candies in basket of percolator and perk.
Or place in heavy cooker and heat slowly, simmering until candies are melted and cider is hot.

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Mix together and serve with raw vegetables such as carrots, broccoli, cauliflower, celery, etc.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: pasta and peas
directions: Chop onion.
Put olive oil in pot just to cover the bottom. Heat the oil, then put in onion and saute until golden brown.
Put in peas and cook until soft, ten to twenty minutes.
Then put a pot of water up for pasta and cook to desired time.
After pasta is ready; drain it, then take the peas and pour it onto the pasta and serve.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix the vinegar and sugar together.
Mix the first 7 ingredients together and let set a few hours.
Add bacon just before serving.

title: cheese fries
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Cool fries according to package directions.
Mix fries and macaroni. Sprinkle with garlic salt.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Heat liquid (vinegar and water), sugar and spice to boiling; add cucumbers. Boil 18 minutes. Pack in jars and seal while hot.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spread into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool and top with the following.

title: no work meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients
well; shape into loaf in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Ovens may vary.

title: cabbage rolls (lebanese style)
directions: Put leaves (a little at
a time) in boiling water until limp; drain.
Mix the remaining ingredients thoroughly (except lemon juice).
Put 1 tablespoon of mixture on each leaf;
roll like a cigar.
Put in pot.
Layer
closely
and
do this until meat mixture is all gone.
Add
salt and pepper to pot.
Place a lid directly on top of
rolls
to
hold
them down (Pyrex is good). Pour boiling water over
the rolls and lid.
Cover the top of pot with another lid.
Cook
over
medium heat on stove for 30 to 35 minutes, then
take
the
first cover off and add lemon juice. Put large cover
on
and cook another 30 minutes until most of the sauce has evaporated.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic.
Drain excess grease off. Add Rotel, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, taco seasoning mix, and chili powder.
Let simmer on low heat for 4 to 5 minutes. Cover bottom of baking dish with corn tortillas (cut into wedges). Pour meat mixture over corn tortillas.
Add another layer of corn tortillas to just cover top of meat mixture.
Whisk milk and cream of mushroom soup together.
Pour over the top of the corn tortillas.
Add all cheese to the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oven rice
directions: Mix all together in a lightly greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: In large saucepan, combine apple cider or juice, brown sugar and nutmeg.
Place cinnamon, allspice and cloves in cheesecloth and tie.
Add to cider mixture.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Serve cider in mugs with orange slices with cloves studded in slices or wedges.

title: apple black walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Beat eggs.
Add oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Fold in black walnuts and diced apples.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Grease heavy pan well.
Put into 375° oven to heat while completing rest of recipe.
Mix all ingredients together and turn into hot pan.
Bake until brown.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar, and chocolate.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, and baking powder.
Add to oil mixture.
Chill overnight.
Roll into balls. Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Bake 350 degrees 10-12 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients next.
Stir until all are well mixed.
Put in 2 large greased bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 layer pans or 1 Bundt pan (greased and floured).
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until done when it springs back.

title: taco salad
directions: In skillet brown hamburger, seasoning and onion.
Drain.
Add kidney beans and cool.
In separate bowl add together shredded lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Mix in meat.
Right before serving, add taco chips and Thousand Island dressing.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Pour over fruit salad.

title: football party dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage. Drain. Add all ingredients and heat until cheese is melted.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir together eggs, sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in two bread pans.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat the butter at medium for 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream; begin and end with flour.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a 10-inch tube pan.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Bring oleo, oil, water and cocoa to boil and add to flour mixture.
Mix together buttermilk and baking soda.
Add to flour mixture with eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: o'henry's
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Mix with peanut butter, peanuts and Rice Krispies.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the chips and spread on top.

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, then layer in order: graham cracker crumbs, coconut, butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour milk over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Immediately run knife around edge of pan.
Cool for 30 minutes, then cut in squares.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers to fine crumbs.
Add powdered sugar, margarine, juices and nuts.
Mix well.
Form into balls and roll on coconut.
May be served frozen.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan; stir in water and
lemon	peel.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and lemon juice.	Yields 6 servings.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Place one piece of chicken between 2 pieces of clear plastic wrap.
Working from the center to the edges, pound lightly with a meat mallet to 1/4-inch thickness. Remove plastic wrap.
Repeat with remaining pieces of chicken.

title: round steak en casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until golden brown.
Arrange onions in bottom of 3-quart casserole.
Cut fat from meat; brown meat on both sides.
Place in casserole on top of onions.
Pour about 1/4 cup of water into drippings; stir, then pour over onions and meat. Add just enough more water to cover onion layer.
Sprinkle parsley, salt, pepper, thyme and marjoram over meat.
Arrange carrots on top.
Cover and bake in a slow oven (300°) for 1 hour. Arrange potatoes and peas over carrots and continue baking in slow oven for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Combine cherries, strawberries, pineapple, sugar and cornstarch; mix well.
Cook on low heat until thick and clear. Remove from heat; add one package of strawberry Jell-O (dry) and pecans.
When cool, put in baked pie shell or graham cracker crust, in which bananas have been sliced.
Top with Cool Whip. This makes enough for 3 pies.
Serves 8.

title: maeder potaeders
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup cereal flakes or any chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: quick broccoli casserole
directions: Cook stalkless broccoli in small amount of water 10 or 12 minutes, just until tender.
Saute onion and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Combine and add mushroom soup (undiluted).
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with margarine.
Bake until it cooks thoroughly. Do not overcook broccoli.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Mix lemon juice with water.
Beat egg yolks; add milk, sugar and butter.
When mix comes to almost a boil, add cornstarch which has been mixed with a little water.

title: bake chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise and seasoning.
Mix chicken in mayonnaise mix. Place chicken mix in refrigerator for 15 to 30 minutes.
Place chicken on broiling pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: susan's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 1 qt. casserole at 350° for 1 hour.
Simple and really easy; may be doubled, tripled, etc.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Roast chicken or turkey.
Cool and remove from the bone. Arrange the meat in the bottom of a cake pan.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix the bread cubes and sauteed onion with seasoning. Make gravy from stock of roasted turkey and pour over the turkey. Place bread cubes on top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: steak marinade
directions: Marinates up to 6 steaks.
Marinate for 6 to 24 hours; turn occasionally.

title: sugar cookies for christmas
directions: Roll out; use cookie cutters.
Bake at 350°.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix sausage, Bisquick and cheese together to make an even blend of ingredients.
Make into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400°
for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
May be frozen, then thawed and cooked.

title: beet pickles
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, water and pickling spice.
Drop cooked and peeled beets into boiling solution and leave until hot through and through.
Remove beets.
Place in jars.
Fill jars with hot solution.
Wipe top of jars with paper towel and seal.

title: scottish kilkenney or irish colcannon(a different version of mashed potatoes)
directions: Put potatoes and rutabaga into a pan of water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook as you would for mashed potatoes.
When tender, add milk and butter; mash.
Excellent served with Grandma Annie Cameron's Sunday-After-Church Roast Beef.
Different variations should include:
shredded carrots, chopped onions or shredded cabbage.
These would be added to the potatoes or potatoes and rutabaga cooked together.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine the ingredients, beating well.
It is best to save about half the milk until all the flour has been added.
Pour about 1 1/2 inches deep in well-greased pan and bake about 1 hour in 325° oven.
Turns dark when done.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: krispy cheese crackers
directions: Mix cheese and oleo.
Add flour, salt and pepper, then cereal. Shape into small balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; mix well.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Cook approximately 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.

title: potato-mushroom casserole(bulgaria)
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Mix all ingredients well in a casserole dish and bake in oven for 40 minutes or until potatoes are cooked. Serve hot or at room temperature. Peas, carrots and peppers may also be added if desired before baking.

title: delicious hot fudge sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, over low heat (or I use double boiler pan) combine condensed milk, semi-sweet chocolate bars, milk, butter and vanilla, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Cool slightly.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni by directions on package. Brown hamburger meat with onion and green pepper.
Add mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Cook on low heat. Drain macaroni; add to hamburger.
Put in casserole dish.
Grate cheese and place on top.
Put in 350° oven until cheese melts and casserole is bubbly.

title: protein pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto hot oiled griddle.
For thinner pancakes, increase amount of water.

title: strawberry banana split pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Turn down TV.
Remove toys from countertop.
Measure 2 cups flour.
Get baking powder.
Remove Benjamin's hand from flour.
Put flour, baking powder and salt into sifter.
Vacuum mixture off kitchen floor (Benjamin spilled).
Get an egg.
Answer telephone.
Separate egg and warm baby Adam's bottle.
Help Mary figure out a new math problem (the old reliable way).
Grease pan:
salesman at door.
Take 1/4-inch of salt from greased pan and look for Benjamin.
Put mess in waste basket, dishes in dishwasher.
Call the bakery.
Take an aspirin.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: *Can use 1 tablespoon lemon juice in sweet milk for sour milk.

title: eggnog pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat well. Add eggs beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with eggnog mix until blended.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into a greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove.
One cup of chopped pecans or walnuts can be added if desired.

title: joyce's spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook very slow for several hours over simmering heat.
Serve over favorite pasta or spaghetti.

title: linguine and clam sauce
directions: Prepare linguine per package directions.
Saute minced garlic in olive oil; add lemon juice and stir in whole and chopped clams, then add dash of red pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Serve over cooked linguine.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Boil the sugar and corn syrup until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and margarine.
Pour over corn flakes.
Stir gently. Wait 15 minutes, then make balls with wet hands. Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Serve cool or room temperature.

title: country rib special
directions: Early in day or day before, heat ribs to boiling in uncovered saucepan with enough water to cover.
Simmer on low for one hour or until fork-tender.
Drain.
Place ribs in barbecue sauce. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Cook 30 minutes on grill or broil or bake in oven.
Be careful not to overcook because meat has been precooked.
It needs only to be well heated through to bring out flavor of marinated meat.
Sieved broth may be used for soup.

title: mushroom spinach salad
directions: Place salad ingredients in a large bowl.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
In a saucepan, combine the last 4 ingredients and cook 1 minute.
Pour over dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper or greased pan.
Let stand until cold.

title: linda's potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Place side by side or in a "fallen domino" pattern in casserole or cake pan.
Add the water.
Cut up margarine in small pieces and place them on the potatoes.
Sprinkle with the dry Italian dressing.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Cook onions, celery and peppers in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with butter.
Beat eggs well in a medium size bowl.
Gradually
beat
in	sugar until mixture is fluffy thick. Stir in
vanilla
and chocolate mixture, then blend in flour and walnuts
until well blended.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake
at
for	30 minutes, or until shiny and firm on	top.
Do
not
overbake;
middle should be fudge-like.	Cool completely, then cut into 2-inch squares.

title: tomato surprise("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Peel and chill rounded tomatoes of even size.
Cut in halves, scoop out centers and drop into each a raw egg.
Dust with salt and pepper.
Cover each with a spoonful of white sauce and then with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° until egg is set.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add flour to creamed mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate pieces with 14 ounces of almond bark over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and peanuts.
Add marshmallows.
Mix.
Pour into greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries and sprinkle with coconut.
Melt remaining almond bark with oil over low heat, stirring until smooth.

title: pineapple, grape and almond salad
directions: Combine pineapple, grapes, almonds and sunflower seeds.
Toss with yogurt.
Tear up spinach and line salad bowl.
Then add pineapple and grape mixture.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Saute hamburger meat with onion; drain grease.
Mix first 8 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 cornmeal batter in first.
Add your hamburger meat, then sprinkle cheese.
Add remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 350°. Let cool for 30 minutes.

title: calico bean casserole #1
directions: Brown cut up bacon slightly. Remove bacon and add hamburger and chopped onion; brown. Into a large casserole, add meat, beans and other ingredients. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a covered casserole. Remove the cover 1/2 hour before casserole is done.

title: mrs. bulkley's basic clear french dressing
directions: To vinegar, add all ingredients except oil.
Shake or blend well, then add oil and mix.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon poppy seed scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a small bowl, soak the currants in the water for 10 minutes.
In a large bowl, whisk the flours, poppy seed, baking powder, baking soda, lemon peel and cinnamon. Using a pastry blender, cut the margarine into the flour mixture until it resembles crumbs.
Stir in the yogurt, egg whites, currants and water and mix well.
The dough should be somewhat sticky and soft.
On a floured surface, roll out the dough until it is 1/2-inch thick, then cut it into rounds using a 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Coat a baking sheet with nonstick spray.
Place the scones on the sheet, leaving about 1/2-inch between them and bake until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yield:
18 scones.

title: linguine and clam sauce
directions: Drain clams; reserve liquid.
Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add flour, stirring constantly. Gradually add clam juice and liquid drained from clams.
Cook and stir over low heat until slightly thickened.
Add clams, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook linguine according to package directions; drain.
Toss individual servings with clam sauce and top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Season meat with salt, pepper and garlic salt and brown in skillet.
Stir in tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
After sauce has simmered, stir in package of cottage cheese.
Pour a portion of sauce into bottom of baking dish; cover with strips of lasagna noodles that have been drained. Add slices of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Top with strips of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
This dish is good to prepare the night before use and take from refrigerator and bake.

title: caldereta
directions: Marinate meat overnight in 1/2 cup vinegar, salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon melted garlic.
Next day, brown beef in olive oil.
Set aside.
Saute onion in olive oil and add tomato sauce.
Brown meat, bay leaf and 1 cup boiling water.
Simmer until tender.
Add liver pate, green chiles, peas, potatoes and sweet peppers. Simmer a few minutes, thicken with bread crumbs.
Check seasoning to taste.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Mix well with sugar, pineapple and pecans.
Add the Cool Whip, folding gently. Pour into baked pie crust.
You can use Sugar Twin and low calorie cream cheese.

title: willie's raleigh house blueberry muffins
directions: Note:
This mixture keeps well in refrigerator.

title: easy chicken cordon blue
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, sprayed with Pam, layer chicken cutlets, ham, cheese and precooked Stove Top stuffing.
Pour chicken broth over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until bubbling. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cauliflower with balsamic vinegar
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the pancetta and cook until softened but not browned, about 3 minutes. Add the cauliflower and saute, stirring frequently, until lightly browned, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
I use slices of cheese (melted) instead of Cheez Whiz.

title: english trifle
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Mix together with Cool Whip.
Add brandy now if using it. Slice cake as normal, then slice in half. Start with layer of cake, the Cool Whip/pudding mix, then layer of each fruit.
Continue layering and end with Cool Whip mixture.
Top with one of the fruits.
Looks beautiful in trifle bowl or clear bowl.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: In food processor, add cheese, pimento and pickles.
Process for 5 seconds.
Scrape sides of bowl with a spatula.
Process 3 to 5 seconds more.
Add remaining ingredients.
Process 5 seconds or until mixture is well blended.

title: greek salad
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl.

title: easy pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet and drain off fat. Blend together in separate bowl soup, sour cream and water. In large rectangular pan, layer 1/2 the potatoes and sauce; salt and
pepper. Top with 1/2 the browned and drained pork chops. Layer with remaining potatoes and sauce; salt and pepper. Top with remaining pork chops. Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add sugar, tomato soup and mix. Add this mixture to the beans that have been placed in casserole. Stir together.
Top with bacon and bake at 350° for one hour or until bubbly throughout.

title: strawberry salad dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add berries, pineapple and bananas.
Chill until partly thickened.
Turn 1/2 of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream on top, then add the remaining gelatin mixture.
Chill several hours or until firm.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add water.
Mix with a fork until off sides.
Roll in small balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Roll while still hot in powdered sugar.

title: brunch coffee cake
directions: Blend butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham and turkey supper
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp, about 10 minutes.
Reserve fat in the pan, drain bacon on paper towel.
Crumble and set aside.
Coarsely chop onion.
Add onion and rice to pan and cook, stirring often for 2 minutes.
Increase heat to medium-high and add tomatoes and juice, broth, thyme, black pepper and bay leaf.
Bring mixture to boil, breaking up tomatoes with a spoon.
Reduce heat to medium-low, cover the pan and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cube the turkey and ham.
Cut bell pepper into thin slivers.
Stir turkey, ham and bell pepper into jambalaya. Cover and cook for about 5 minutes until pepper is limp.

title: meat-n-cheese toasties
directions: Brown the beef and sausage.
Drain the fat off.
Melt in the cheese.
Stir well.
Place a spoonful on each slice of cocktail rye.
Place on cookie sheet in oven at 400° about 10 minutes or until bread is toasty.

title: cinnamon raisin english muffins
directions: Sift together 1 1/2 cups of flour, yeast and cinnamon.
Heat milk, water, raisins, sugar, oil and salt over low heat until just warm.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Stir in more flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured board. Knead until manageable (3 minutes).
Cover with bowl.
Rest 30 minutes.
Roll out on corn meal or flour until 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into 3 to 4-inch circles.
Place on buttered cookie sheet sprinkled with corn meal or flour.
Let raise 30 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: strawberry glace pie
directions: Mash enough strawberries to measure 1 cup.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water and mashed strawberries gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute, cool. Beat cream cheese until smooth; spread on bottom of pie shell. Fill shell with whole strawberries.
Pour cooled strawberry mixture over whole berries.
Refrigerate until set; at least 3 hours.

title: peachesy pie
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar with peach slices, cornstarch, corn syrup, pumpkin pie spice and vanilla.
Set aside cheese cake topping.
Combine eggs, 1/3 cup sugar, lemon juice and 2 tablespoons peach syrup in saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Soften cream cheese. Blend in sour cream.
Add hot mixture.
Beat smooth.
Pour in crust and bake.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as directed on box. Spray a 3-quart casserole dish with a nonstick spray.
After the macaroni is cooked, drain off water and add salt, pepper and butter or margarine.
Mix milk, egg and cheese together, then add the macaroni.
Place into casserole dish.
Pour on the milk mixture and bake until bubbly and golden brown, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Whip together by hand and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: easy good frosting
directions: Beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Slowly add the powdered sugar, beat well.
Add the 1/4 c. butter or Crisco and mix well. Add flavoring, salt and food coloring, mix.
Spread on a completely cooled cake.
This frosting freezes well.

title: zesty chicken breasts
directions: Preheat grill to medium (if using gas grill), or until charcoal is covered with gray ash and is medium-hot.
In a small saucepan, combine vinegar, water, margarine, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and pepper;
bring to a boil.
Place chicken on heated grill.
Brush with half of sauce, grill for 8 minutes.
Turn over and baste with remaining sauce.
Grill 7-8 minutes longer or until internal juices run clear.	Serve.

title: herb and shrimp spread
directions: Beat together cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Add next 4 ingredients; mix well.
With a spoon, fold in shrimp.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with assorted vegetables and crackers.
Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Cube angel food cake to make and place in a glass dish. Combine instant vanilla pudding, milk and vanilla ice cream.
Pour over cubed cake.
Chill.
Combine strawberry Jell-O and hot water. While still hot, put in frozen strawberries.
Pour over the cake, chill and serve.
Serves 12.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Sprinkle with nutmeg on top.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. Melt butter and pour into bottom of casserole dish. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top of melted butter. Top with spaghetti, sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° until top layer of cheese is melted, approximately 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind up Oreo cookies in a blender and set aside.
Mix cream cheese with butter and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and mix well and set aside.
Mix vanilla pudding with milk.
When thick, blend into the Cool Whip mixture.
Cover the hole of a clean flowerpot with a small plastic lid.
Alternate layers of the Oreo crumbs and cream-pudding mixture, ending with Oreo crumbs.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 to 2 days.
Prior to eating dinner, cover the stems of some cut flowers with plastic wrap and insert them into the dirt cake.
Use as a centerpiece during dinner, then remove the flowers and enjoy.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice unpeeled zucchini.
Simmer in a little water for 3 to 6 minutes.
In a casserole dish, combine sour cream, butter and cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Add zucchini and mix gently to coat.
Sprinkle with crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tootsie's fudge pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and cocoa; stir well.
Add beaten eggs and milk; stir well.
Do not beat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25-30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then add Pet milk, sweet milk and water.
Cook until lightly thickened, then add vanilla and cook until thicker.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Cook garlic in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add broth and tortellini; heat to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Add spinach and tomatoes. Simmer 5 minutes or more.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make sure waffle iron is hot.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix coconut, flour, cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Put 1/2 of mixture on bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pat down.
Then put on cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle other 1/2 of crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice separately.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add soup and water.
Add cheese and seasonings and stir until cheese is melted.
Add rice and broccoli and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until warm.

title: mama mia's pralines
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, milk and pecans in heavy pot over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and margarine.
Allow to cool for 5 minutes, then stir until it thickens.
Drop from end of spoon in desired size.
(Work quickly, as it will harden rapidly.)

title: easy microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and white syrup, microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir in roasted peanuts, microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla, microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir gently until light and foamy.
Spread on lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Cool 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: lemon layer delight
directions: Blend together flour, butter and pecans.
Pat out this mixture smoothly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Blend together cream cheese, 1/2 bowl Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
