Beat the pudding and milk until thick, 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour the lemon instant pudding mixture on top of the Philadelphia cream cheese and Cool Whip layer.
Place other half bowl Cool Whip on top of this layer and sprinkle with nuts.
Cool overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator for one week or more.

title: banana chicken salad
directions: Dice bananas, pineapple, celery and chicken.
Mix bananas and pineapple together to prevent discoloration of the bananas. Lightly add other ingredients.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with chopped nuts and ripe or stuffed olives.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ma's fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Soften the cream cheese.
Mix mayo, sugar and cream cheese with mixer until smooth.
Fold in well drained fruit, then Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Cover and serve 12 to 24 hours later.
Add coconut or sprinkle with walnuts, if desired.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil fryer for 1 hour or cook until done.
Cool, debone and cut into large pieces.
Mix melted margarine and stuffing together; spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of stuffing.
Mix soups with 2 cans of broth that chicken was cooked in.
Pour soup over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brussels sprouts with green grapes
directions: Clean Brussels sprouts; strip off any yellow leaves and slice off ends.
Partially cook in boiling water until not quite tender (about 5 minutes).
Drain.
Return well drained sprouts, grapes and 2 tablespoons butter to pan.
Season with salt and pepper. Heat until butter is melted and sizzling.
Pour in cream; reduce heat to low and cook sprouts until cream has almost evaporated completely, about 10 minutes.
Dot with 1 or 2 tablespoons more butter.

title: veggie squares
directions: Finely chop vegetables and sprinkle on top of crescent rolls. You can use celery, cauliflower, broccoli, green onions, shredded carrots, etc.
Blend ingredients well with vegetables and place on top of cooled crescent crust.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Drain medium size can crushed pineapple.
Bring juice to boil and dissolve Jell-O, then add ice cream to mixture.
Stir until melted.
Add pineapple and let set until firm.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: coconut mist cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: velveeta cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add chunks of Velveeta cheese and the can of green chilies and chopped tomatoes.
Melt and serve with Doritos.
A crock-pot works well.

title: easy brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Repeat, using the remaining bread, sausage and cheese.
Slightly beat the eggs (I use a wire eggbeater) in a large mixing bowl.
Add the salt, pepper and dry mustard.
(I sift the dry mustard as I add it; it is hard to blend.)
Beat to blend.
Add the milk.
Beat again and pour over the layers.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Parboil in boiling, salted water. Drain.
Mix with bread crumbs, cheese and bacon (which has been fried and fat poured off).
Beat eggs.
Add milk and combine with eggplant mixture.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 325° oven until set and brown.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a pan sprayed with Pam, 9 x 13-inch.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: taco sauce
directions: *One (16 ounce) can stewed tomatoes may be substituted.

title: easy italian casserole
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic until brown; drain.
Stir in sauce, mushrooms, sugar, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes. Heat oven to 400°.
Grease or use Pam in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix Bisquick with milk and egg; spread 1/2 of mixture in dish. Top with 4 slices of cheese.
Spoon beef mixture over cheese. Place pepperoni on top.
Top with 4 slices of cheese.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Drop remaining Bisquick mixture on top.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Saute in butter the onion and bell pepper. Add ground beef and cook until browned.
Stir in tomato paste, catsup and water.
Add all other ingredients. Cover and simmer on low heat for 10 minutes. Cook spaghetti until tender.
Rinse and drain.
Spread meat sauce over spaghetti for individual servings.

title: roast shallot potatoes
directions: Oil a shallow baking pan and place shallots in single row. Bake at 350° under tender, approximately 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and place in blender or food processor until smooth.
Blend heavy cream into shallots in blender or processor.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken in a lot of water.
Debone chicken and return to broth.

title: bog stew(crock-pot)
directions: In a lightly greased frying pan or skillet, saute green peppers and onions until tender.
Add ground beef.
Mix in salt, black pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Stir and let simmer for five minutes.
Add tomato sauce and cook over medium fire for 10 to 15 minutes until meat is thoroughly cooked.

title: italian butterfly pork chops
directions: Lightly season chops with garlic powder, black pepper and Italian seasoning. Dice sausage, onion and mushrooms. Mix sausage, onion, mushrooms, tomato sauce and 1/2 pound cheese. Stuff mixture into chops. Use toothpicks to hold together. Cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 400° (until done). Fifteen minutes before done, sprinkle the rest of cheese on chops.

title: shaggy dog
directions: Roast marshmallows until golden brown.
Roll in one or more of the remaining ingredients.

title: unbaked icebox cream
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add egg, cream, pineapple, salt and nuts.
Beat well.
In a Pyrex dish, place a layer of wafers and then filling alternately.
Place in refrigerator.
Before serving put whipped cream on top.

title: quick dessert(peaches with meringue)
directions: Mix peaches and almonds and cover with a standard recipe of meringue and bake at 325° until lightly browned.
Cool before serving.

title: sydney dalton's kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and egg yolks until creamy; set aside.
Sift together the flour and cinnamon; set aside.
Mix the oil, hot water and pineapple.
Alternately add 1/4 of each mixture, blending well and continuing until contents of all 3 bowls are mixed.
Add the nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar and pineapple juice.
Pour over the warm cake.

title: black forest cake
directions: Cook cake mix in 9-inch cake pans, then let cool.
Cut into small squares, then take a big bowl and put cut up cake in the bottom first, then add cherry pie filling, a little at a time, then add Cool Whip, a few tablespoons at a time.
Layer the cake, cherry pie filling, and Cool Whip until all the ingredients are used up.
Finish with Cool Whip.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed on box.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Blend in flour; add milk gradually.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Add cheese and lemon juice.
Stir well.
Add chicken and sauce to rice.
Mix well. Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice set aside. Fry bacon; add all other ingredients except soy sauce. Cook until veggies are tender; add rice and mix. Add soy sauce. Cook 5 mins. on low.

title: plain cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening 10 minutes at high speed of mixer. Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour; add salt.
Add alternately with milk at a lower speed.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°, then increase heat to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Rinse strawberries, cut off green stems; put aside.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and Cool Whip until smooth (some lumps may remain if cream cheese is not room temperature).
In large dessert bowl, layer vanilla wafers in the bottom, glaze, Cool Whip mixture and top with strawberries and cookies.
Repeat steps, the top should end up with strawberries on top and around the bowl.
Sprinkle sugar on strawberries if desired.

title: egg noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together until a very stiff dough is formed.
Roll dough out until paper thin using lots of flour.
Let dry for awhile.
Roll into a roll and cut into desired size, fine or larger strips.
Let dry.
If not used at once, put into freezer bags and freeze.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Boil juice from pineapple and cherries.
Pour over Jell-O. Add Coke.
When it begins to gel, add fruit and nuts.
Very good with ham or turkey.

title: quick saucy chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add vegetables and garlic; stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove vegetables from pan.
Add remaining oil and chicken to pan; stir-fry 4 minutes or until tender.
Stir in vegetables, Miracle Whip salad dressing, soy sauce and ginger; simmer 1 minute, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot onion dip
directions: Bake in 2 small rectangular foil loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook mixture (first 4 ingredients) to form hair on spoon (hard crack).
Remove from heat; add butter.
Pour over popcorn.
Wet hands in cold water.
Make balls.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and peanut butter. Blend in sugar. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust and freeze. Makes 3 pies.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Dump 1 can applesauce into pan. Dump 1 can crushed pineapple on top of that.
Spread cake mix over that.
Melt butter and pour over top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over butter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add crushed bananas, then sifted flour with soda.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Mix
the
onion
soup mix, Russian dressing and apricot preserves.	Stir
in
the
chicken.
Spread
in a 10 x 15-inch glass baking dish.	Cover.	Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Whip cream and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and fold into whipped cream.
Place mixture in cooked and cooled pie crust. Top with can of cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate for several hours before cutting.

title: best ever carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl, then mix in oil and eggs.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Grease a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan and bake 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and ice.

title: fondue shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp.
Blend until smooth. Stir in shrimp.
Pour into fondue pot.
Keep mixture warm over low heat.

title: working woman's pickles(sweet)
directions: Pack 1 gallon of cucumbers into glass jar (preferably 1 gallon glass jar).
Add salt; fill jar with vinegar.
Let stand 6 weeks. Then take out of jar, wash thoroughly and cut in rings.
Put back in same jar.
Add pickling spices and sugar.
Set jar aside. Shake occasionally to make syrup.
You can keep in refrigerator or put in pint jars.
Delicious sweet pickles.
No cooking.
Anyone can do this.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot.
Cook 4 to 5 hours over low heat.
Remove onion and chicken bones (strip chicken).
Serve with a loaf of rye bread (optional!).

title: fried okra(what a wonderful way to eat okra!  use fresh, not frozen!)
directions: Serve these instead of a baked potato with steaks when Vidalias are available!

title: easy punch(sugar-free and low-fat)
directions: Mix well and serve over ice or add ice cubes before serving.

title: chunky cheese spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in oil in large skillet until no longer pink (about 5 minutes).
Remove chicken from pan; drain all but 1 tablespoon oil.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add pineapple.
Slice bananas on top of mix.
Put marshmallows on top of bananas.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, let harden in refrigerator.

title: santa claus punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine drink mix with sugar, cranberry juice and ice with water.
Stir until well dissolved.
Makes 16 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: happy day
directions: Measure words carefully.
Add heaping cups of understanding. Use generous amounts of time and patience.
Cook on front burner. Keep temperature low.
Do not boil! Add dash of humor and pinch of warm personality.
Season to taste with spice of life.
Serve in individual molds.

title: no cook white frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.

title: tuna roll
directions: Mix 4 tablespoons parsley with remaining ingredients in bowl. Shape into a roll and chill until firm.
Roll into the remaining 2 tablespoons of parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: smoky peas and new potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes covered in small amount boiling water about 12 minutes.
Add peas to potatoes; cook 3 more minutes.
Drain.
Add flour and milk to melted margarine.
Cook until thickened. Decrease heat.
Add cheeses to flour mixture.
Mix until melted. Add cheese mixture to potatoes and peas.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Crumble bacon on top.
Serve immediately or warm in oven.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Pour evenly into 3 or 4 ungreased 1 pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Do not drain corn.
Combine all ingredients.
Do not cook macaroni.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.
Melt cheese, if desired, over top.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut hot potatoes in half lengthwise. Scoop out potato, leaving skins intact for restuffing. Beat potato, with cottage cheese, milk, and onion. Spoon mixture back into skins. Sprinkle with pepper, paprika and parsley flakes. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes or until golden. Makes 8 servings.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; let chill.
Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale.
Yields 14 (8 ounce) servings.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Cut nuts and cherries; cut marshmallows in quarters.
Crush graham crackers until fine.
Mix all ingredients well except milk. Add milk.
Pack in waxed paper-lined pan.
Chill overnight. Serve with whipped cream.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown sausage and drain off the fat.
Mix other ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Add sausage.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses and dressing mix well and chill. Form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans. Serve with crackers.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain fruit; use juices plus enough water to make 2 cups liquid with pudding.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip and fruit.
Can add orange food coloring for more color.

title: miracle pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender; blend well.
Pour into oiled 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Then the miracle: Crust will be on the bottom, pie filling in center and coconut topping above.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion together and drain.
Add remaining ingredients except crackers; mix well and pour into a 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed Ritz and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together and beat well.
Put in pie crust and bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cut roast into thin strips.
Put meat and 1 cup water into saucepan.
Boil out all water.
Add can of mushrooms to meat and brown.
In separate pot, boil noodles; drain.
Leave in colander. Mix can of mushroom soup and cup of milk until smooth.
Blend all ingredients into soup.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: chicken soppa
directions: Boil chicken; remove meat and save broth.
Blend cans of cream of chicken soup, large can of canned milk and can of chicken broth.
Dip tortillas in hot fat, then dip in soup mixture and layer in the bottom of a 2-inch deep casserole dish.
Sprinkle with onion, chilies, cheese and chicken pieces.
Spoon soup sauce over this.
Continue until all tortillas are used (three layers). Cover with remaining sauce and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbling (about 30 minutes).

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sugar, oil and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Combine vegetables.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over them.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: buttermilk rice pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender in order given.
Blend until well mixed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 or 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, salt and cornstarch, adding a little milk at a time, stirring well.
Add rest of milk in water.
Heat until boiling, stirring continuously.
After gravy is thick, remove from heat and add margarine.

title: grandma's macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl, empty salad dressing into bowl, gradually pouring evaporated milk, stirring constantly.
Stir until smooth. Finely chop onion and green pepper and grate carrot; stir into mixture.
Finally, cook Creamettes according to package directions; cool by running under cold water in colander.
Add to mixture; mix well. Season to taste.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix vegetables, chicken and soup in 9-inch plate (spray with Pam).
Stir remaining ingredients until blended; pour into pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: maryann sawyer's wassail
directions: Combine ingredients; except oranges; heat until steaming. Precook whole oranges (however many you want to float in your punch bowl) by boiling for 10 minutes.
Stick with whole cloves; float in punch bowl.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix milk and both soups together. Put meat and onions in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and spread Tater Tots over meat.
Pour soup mixture over Tater Tots.
Heat oven to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.
Add cheese on top and bake another 5 minutes.

title: corn relish 1933
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Chop cabbage, onions, peppers and celery fine.
Mix all ingredients and bring to a full, rolling boil. Boil for 20 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.
Invert jars until cool.

title: cucumber mousse
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, gelatine, salt and vinegar in boiling water. Chill until like egg whites.
Beat until very fluffy.
Add mayonnaise, cucumbers, onion and sour cream.
Pour into molds. Chill.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread each muffin half with tomato sauce.
Add any or all of other ingredients.
Top with cheeses. Put in oven (or microwave) until cheeses are melted.

title: pioneer potato candy
directions: Combine potatoes, salt and vanilla in a 4-quart mixing bowl. Sift powdered sugar over potatoes.
Cover with damp cloth and set until chilled.
Shape into small balls.
Dip into melted chocolate.
Roll into nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: taco dip
directions: Mash avocados and lemon juice and set aside.
Mix salt, pepper, sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix and set aside.
These can be shaped any way that looks good on cake plate or pizza pan (looks like a pizza when done).
Make layers as such:
1st bean dip, 2nd avocado mix, 3rd sour cream.
Sprinkle these next: onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Serve with taco chips.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 stick melted butter and graham crumbs.
Beat egg, 1 1/2 sticks butter and powdered sugar for 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Add sliced bananas that have been dipped in pineapple juice.
Add crushed pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip; sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Mash sweet potatoes in a bowl.
Add drained pineapple, butter, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and milk.
Stir to blend.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes (until warmed through) at 350°.
Place marshmallows on top and bake approximately 15 more minutes until marshmallows are slightly melted and golden brown.

title: baked custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat slightly 2 eggs.
Stir in evaporated milk, water, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Pour into 4 custard cups.
Set in shallow pan containing 1 inch of hot water. Bake about 45 minutes or until knife inserted near edge of custard comes out clean.
Cool.

title: salmon loaf majestic
directions: Drain salmon.
Reserve liquid.
Pour milk over bread crumbs and let stand 5 minutes.
Add flaked salmon, liquid, eggs, onion, lemon juice, parsley and seasonings.
Spoon into oiled loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until firm.
Unmold.
Serve plain or sauced.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: appetizer(very good)
directions: Roll sausage into 1-inch balls.
Place on jelly roll pan. Bake at 500° until done (about 7 minutes).
Melt jelly and mustard together.
Add sausage balls.
Serve warm in chafing dish.

title: corn au gratin
directions: Saute onion
and
green pepper in butter for 5 minutes. Add flour,
seasonings	and milk; stir constantly until smooth and thick.
Combine
this
mixture
with
corn and beaten egg. Put mixture into shallow casserole.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs; brown in a moderate oven at 350° to 375°.

title: apple cake
directions: Core, peel and slice 4 large apples.
Mix together sugar and eggs.
Add oil and beat 1 minute.
Sift together soda, salt and baking powder, cinnamon and flour.
Fold dry ingredients into liquid.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Lastly, fold in apples.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream and nuts when cool.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Place sliced cucumbers and onion in flat 9 x 13-inch plastic container with lid.
Mix together the last 4 ingredients; pour over cucumbers.
Marinate overnight.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg with a beater until fluffy.
Beat in remaining ingredients just until smooth.
For thinner pancakes, stir in an additional 1/4 cup milk.
Pour 3 tablespoons for each pancake. Makes 9 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: rick's favorite birthday cake
directions: Mix all and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
(I have used 9 x 13-inch pan in past.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes for 9 x 13-inch and one hour for a Bundt pan.

title: chicken cheese casserole
directions: Boil whole chicken or chicken breasts until done.
Break chicken into pieces and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use 1 package Swiss cheese and layer pieces on top of chicken.
Mix milk or chicken broth with cream of chicken soup.
Pour over cheese.
Mix Stove Top stuffing mix according to package directions.
Layer over top of soup and chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new york style pizza buns
directions: Put cooked hamburg, tomato paste, oregano, sugar, salt and water in frying pan.
Simmer until thick.

title: sparkling cranberry float
directions: Combine cranberry juice, apple juice and ginger ale.
Pour mixture into glasses and top each with a scoop of sherbet.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef, peppers and garlic in 1/4 cup cooking oil until beef is no longer pink. Add rest of ingredients and simmer.

title: spicy chicken pita
directions: Cut chicken in small strips and marinate in teriyaki sauce 30 minutes or more.
Combine thyme and next 4 ingredients in small bowl.
Heat olive oil and saute onion in large skillet.
Add chicken and stir-fry over medium/hot heat.
Sprinkle spices over chicken and cook until done.
(May use 1/2 of the spice mixture for less peppery taste).
Combine mayonnaise and horseradish; spread in pita.
Add chicken and lettuce.
Good, easy and spicy!

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Simmer chicken breasts until tender; bone, dice and save stock.
Line bottom and sides of well-greased 3-quart casserole with 6 tortillas, cut up.
Sprinkle with 2 or more tablespoons chicken stock.
Combine soups, onion, green pepper and chili powder.
Pour half of this mixture, half of chicken and half of cheese on tortillas.
Make a second layer of tortillas, chicken, soup mixture and cheese.
Top last layer of cheese with can of Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until hot and bubbly.
May be prepared in advance and reheated.
Serves 12.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Mix melted margarine, brown sugar, granulated sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in oatmeal and cornflakes.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and add to first mixture.
(I add 1/2 cup raisins or chocolate chips.)
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 14 minutes.

title: apple-broccoli salad
directions: Core and chop apples. Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook the tomatoes and onions together. Run through colander. Make a paste of the remaining ingredients.
Add to tomatoes and boil for 1 to 2 minutes to thicken.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Melt butter and place half in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Crush crackers (Town House will do) and place half in casserole.
Add half of the chicken on cracker layer.
Add chestnuts after cutting them into slivers.
Mix soups and sour cream in a bowl and pour half over layers.
Add another layer of chicken, chestnuts, soups and crackers.
Dribble remaining butter over crackers.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: simply meat loaf
directions: In a bowl combine eggs, gravy mix, garlic, black pepper, worcestershire sauce and ground beef; mix well.
Add finely diced onions and green peppers.
Crumble crackers finely with your hands. Form 2 loaves by molding into logs.
Place in 2 glass loaf pans. With your four fingers make an indentation about 2 inches deep the length of the pan.
Drizzle ketchup over meat loaf.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour 35 minutes.

title: kielbasa stew
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, cut bacon into 2-inch pieces. Thinly slice carrots and potatoes.
Cut broccoli into 2 x 1/2-inch pieces.
Cut onion into thin wedges.
Slice kielbasa crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel the shrimp, leaving on the last shell segment and tail. Devein the shrimp.
Rinse the shrimp under cold running water and pat well with paper towels to dry.
In a heavy, nonreactive skillet, large enough to hold the shrimp in a single layer, heat the oil over med-high heat.
When the oil is hot, but not smoking, add the shrimp.
Toss the shrimp to coat with the oil and cook about 3 minutes.
Remove the shrimp to a warm plate and tent with foil to keep warm.
Add the garlic to the pan along with parsley and basil and cook, stirring 1 minute.
Add the lemon juice and the white wine and cook 1 minute more.
Add one piece of butter at a time, stirring constantly.
When one piece has melted add the next until all are added.
Remove from the heat and season with salt and pepper.
To serve, line up 4 shrimp on each of 2 warm serving plates.
Spoon sauce equally over shrimp.

title: spicy rice fillets
directions: In skillet, heat oil and brown ocean fillets and cut pieces in thirds.
Add the peppers, onions and garlic.
Simmer about 2 minutes.
Add brown rice and salsa.
Stir carefully, do not break the fillets.
Simmer about 5 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add broccoli.
Add cornbread mix and mix well; pour into 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: rave reviews coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed with mixer for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook onion and garlic in margarine until transparent.
Brown ground meat.
Add flour.
Cook about 5 minutes over low heat.
Add salt, pepper, mushrooms and cream of mushroom soup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat through.
Serve immediately. Don't boil the sour cream.
Serve over egg noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: *24 hour cabbage slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion, green pepper, olives and sugar. Combine remaining ingredients and boil for 3 minutes.
Pour hot dressing over cabbage mixture.
Cover and chill for 24 hours. This slaw keeps well in the refrigerator for several days.
Serves 12.

title: haupia
directions: Pour coconut milk in saucepan.
Combine sugar and cornstarch. Stir in water; blend well.
Stir sugar mixture into coconut milk; cook and stir over low heat until thick.
Pour into 8-inch square pan; chill.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: sausage bread
directions: Roll dough to oblong (17 x 11-inch).
Brown sausage, mushrooms, onions and peppers.
Drain and spread over dough. Sprinkle with cheese and pepperoni.
Fold edges together.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Serve with spaghetti sauce, if wanted.

title: grandma's sweet rabbit
directions: Flour rabbit and brown along with the onion.
Drain off excess fat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add brown sugar (sprinkle generously over the meat).
Cook until tender.
You may want to add a little water.

title: brownies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, chocolate and vanilla. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk. Stir in nuts. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.
When cooled, you can sprinkle powdered sugar if you prefer.

title: golden pineapple casserole
directions: Drain
pineapple,
reserving
cup
juice.
In mixing bowl, combine
pineapple,
juice, sugar, flour and eggs.
Mix well. Spoon
into 2-quart baking dish.
Top with bread cubes. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes or until set and browned. Serve
as
side
dish with ham or poultry.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir in butter, then eggs, then Parmesan.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread Ricotta over bottom of crust.

title: cherry whip
directions: Mix together in large bowl pineapple and milk.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Fold in cherry pie filling; mix in nuts. Refrigerate until firm.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Use one cup of crumbs in bottom of pan.
Beat margarine, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Spread over crumbs.
Add strawberries over mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts and remaining cup of crumbs.
Cover with whipped cream.
Let stand overnight.

title: cranberry-apple mold
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Cool until partially set. Then add last 4 ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart mold.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: kraut burgers
directions: Cook hamburger; drain off fat.
Add onion and sauerkraut. Cook together 1/2 hour.
Have yeast bread ready to make into buns. Roll out flat and divide into large flat buns.
Place large spoonful of meat mixture in center of bun and fold over.
Let rolls rise.
Bake until brown.
Lightly butter tops and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo. Add cream of chicken soup, milk and Velveeta cheese.
Heat until cheese melts. Fold in 3 cups cooked rice and thawed (not cooked) broccoli.
Pour into greased shallow casserole.
Put strips of Velveeta cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: perfect white bread
directions: Pour warm water in large bowl and sprinkle with yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and lukewarm milk to the yeast mixture and beat in about 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth and falls from spoon in sheets.
With a spoon and 1 hand, mix in enough flour to make dough that pulls away from sides, leaving only small amount sticking to sides.

title: round steak rolls
directions: Thin slice steak.
Roll each slice around slices of onion or green pepper.
Secure with toothpicks.
Brown rolls in oil.
In another pot, dissolve bouillon cubes in 3-inches of water.
Add salt, pepper, meat and meat drippings.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and cream of tartar.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Roll out and use in any pie recipe.
Makes 2 single crusts or 1 double crust.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and onion flakes.
Put hash browns in 9 x 13-inch pan and spread with soup mixture.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over mixture.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over cheese, then drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove and add Hershey's Kisses and cook 2 minutes longer.

title: raisin squares
directions: Cover raisins with water and boil until puffy, about 20 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, spices and milk.
Add flour to raisins covering each well. Add remaining ingredients.

title: pronto pups
directions: Mix thoroughly with mixer.
Insert fudgsicle stick into wiener and dip in batter.
Cook in hot, deep fat about 3 minutes.

title: crabmeat puffs
directions: Beat egg white in small bowl.
Add seasonings and fold in crabmeat.
Pile on Melba toast rounds.
Sprinkle with paprika and place on cookie sheet.
When ready to serve, place under broiler 3 minutes or until puffy and light brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine onion and celery in butter and saute.
Add flour.
Add fluid and sour cream to make a white sauce.
Add tender broccoli; simmer.
Put contents, mostly broccoli, in a blender for a few seconds to puree, then put back into pan.
Top with grated cheese in bowl.

title: plum cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix with mixer.
In separate bowl, sift flour, cloves and cinnamon. Add flour mixture and plums, alternating, until well blended. Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: amanda's vegetarian chili
directions: Cook onion in broth for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: garden relish
directions: I cook all together about 25 minutes.
I use 6 heads of cabbage for 6 to 7 jars.
Measure 2 cups at a time.
Add the other ingredients to match the 2 cups of cabbage.

title: carrot cake #2
directions: Mix oil and eggs.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add pineapple, carrots, vanilla and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika; mix well.
Pat 1 teaspoon dough mixture around each olive, covering it completely.
Arrange on a baking sheet and freeze firm.
Place in 3 or 4 plastic bags and return to freezer.
When ready to bake, preheat oven to 400° and bake 15 minutes.

title: mrs. murphy's 7-minute fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put on stove to boil.
When boiling, time for 7 minutes, stirring from time to time.
Remove from stove and beat until creamy.
Then add nuts and continue beating.
Then add Marshmallow Creme.
Continue beating until firm enough to set.

title: night before casserole
directions: Combine all
ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and let set for 30 to 60 minutes.
Very good!

title: pizza look crab spread
directions: Cream cheese until soft; add onion, garlic salt and lemon juice.
Spread thinly on platter (dinner plate size).
On top of cream cheese mixture, pour chili sauce and spread evenly.
Next sprinkle drained crab meat.
Top with parsley.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Blend in egg and applesauce.
Combine baking soda and boiling water.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
Add water mixture alternately with flour mixture.
Blend in chopped walnuts.
Bake one hour at 350° in 8 x 12-inch oblong pan.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and onion together.
Pour sugar over and let stand while preparing following dressing:

title: rice croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; mold into balls.
Fry in hot canola oil until brown.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Day Before:
Mix together sour cream, taco mix and mayonnaise. Refrigerate overnight.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix bread and milk in bowl, add sugar, butter, cinnamon, salt, vanilla, and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in raisins.
Pour mixture into greased 2 quart casserole and bake 1 hr.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemon juice and condensed milk together.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate about 1 hour before serving.

title: nacho chicken
directions: Combine soup and 1 cup cheese, chilies and onions.
Stir together nonfat dry milk and flour.
Add water to make 2/3 cup. Add to soup mixture and stir.
Layer 1/3 cup chips in 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
Top with 1/2 chicken and 1/2 soup mixture.
Repeat. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake in 350°
oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with chips and garnish with tomato wedges after baking.

title: never fail fudge(holiday recipe)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cut up margarine and chocolate chips. Grease a jelly roll pan lightly and line with wax paper. In a large saucepan, combine the sugar, cream of tartar, salt and evaporated milk. Mix well and cook over moderate heat to a bubbly boil. Then time for exactly 6 minutes. Remove from heat and pour over margarine and chocolate chips. Stir until dissolved. Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into pan at room temperature, then put in refrigerator for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Then cut into pieces.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add soup, enchilada sauce mix, bouillon cubes, chili beans, salt and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix well and simmer for 10 minutes.
Put half of mixture in baking dish. Top with tortillas torn into bite size pieces, then layer of sour cream, then grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: muffins
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
In a bowl, mix the beaten egg, milk and Wesson oil.
Add the dry ingredients.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot grapefruit toddy
directions: Mix juice by package directions.
Place sugar, 2 cinnamon sticks and cloves in pan.
Add juice.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Pour into mugs.
Serve with cinnamon stick stirrers.
Makes 12 cups.

title: wine slush
directions: Mix all.
Freeze 12 to 24 hours.
Fill glass 3/4 full of slush mix from freezer (do not unfreeze).
Add 7-Up or Squirt pop to fill glass.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Bring water to	a
boil; add rice and soup mix.
Cook 5 minutes and set aside.
Brown sausage and remove from pan.	In the drippings,	saute
the onion, bell pepper and celery.
Add to rice
mixture
and
sausage.
Add	mushroom
soup.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cabbage scramble
directions: Heat margarine in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 5 to 8 minutes or until done.
Stir sparingly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift half the flour over the fruit and nuts and mix.
Mix together rest of dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with grape juice.
Add fruit and nuts. Pour batter in loaf pans that are greased and lined with brown paper or use a tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours if using big pans and 3 hours if using small pans.
Wrap in wine soaked cloth and place in tight containers for a month or 2 before eating.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: "tony" cookies
directions: Melt chips in top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Crush the flakes to 1 1/2 cups.
Set aside.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Measure margarine and sugar into bowl and beat until very light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients, mix thoroughly.
Fold in crushed flakes.
Swirl warm melted chocolate lightly through batter, leaving streaks of chocolate.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Wash, scrape and cut carrots into thick slices.
Cook in salt water until barely tender, do not overcook.
Into large bowl put sliced onion, sliced pepper and sliced zucchini and drained, cooked carrots.
In pan, put in soup, sugar, salad oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, then pour over vegetables.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.
Will keep two weeks.

title: 4 cheese pasta and beef
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Brown meat; salt and pepper to taste. (Drain grease.)
Add tomatoes; cook, uncovered, until slightly thickened.
Stir in onions and cream cheese.
Toss in pasta and put cheeses on top.
Put in oven until cheese melts at 350°.

title: salata(mixed green salad)
directions: Rub a wooden salad bowl with cut clove of garlic.
Break lettuce into bite size pieces.
Add the remaining vegetables and herbs.
Add some dressing; toss together lightly with a wooden spoon.

title: tom pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Blend sugar, butter and Crisco with mixer.
Add cup milk and half the eggs and flour alternately. Add flavoring.
Pour in pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
When finished in oven, dump on rack, then back on plate.

title: chocolate-pecan pie
directions: Mix milk, butter and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Heat until chocolate melts.
Cool slightly, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Crush Doritos in bottom of greased 9x13 pan. Brown ground beef; drain and add on top of doritos. Chop onion on top of beef. Top onion with 1/2 of grated cheese; then top with both soups. Ro-Tel tomatoes and water. Using spatula, drag through top mixtures to lightly mix. Put remaining cheese on top. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Make this a family project to look up all the ingredients. All are found in the Bible (King James Version).

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Drain thawed strawberries and pineapple.
Save juice.
Mix jello with boiling water.
Use drained liquid and cold water to equal 6 cups; add jello.
Let set until like egg whites.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Pour half of the mixture in a large sheet cake pan.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: In a skillet, saute onions and green pepper in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup, drained mushrooms and pimientos and basil; set aside.

title: veal chops with mustard sauce
directions: In 1 pan, saute shallots in 2 tablespoons of butter; set aside. Wipe surface of chops with damp cloth and sprinkle with flour.
In a large skillet, heat remaining butter and olive oil until sizzling hot.
Saute chops quickly until golden.
Reduce heat and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper chops.
Place chops in oven pan.
Heat oven to 400°.
Add wine to skillet and reduce to syrupy consistency.
Pour over chops.
Place shallots around chops.
Cover and cook in oven 20 to 30 minutes until tender.
Remove chops to warmed platter.
Add cream and bring to a simmer.
Add mustard and stir well.
Do not simmer.
Cover chops with sauce and serve.

title: swedish tea ring
directions: Soften yeast in water. Combine scalded milk, salt, sugar and shortening. When lukewarm, add yeast and half the flour and beat well. Let rise until very light, then add egg and remaining flour and mix well. Let rise. Roll dough into a rectangular sheet on a lightly floured board. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with nuts. Roll up like a jelly roll and form into a ring on greased baking sheet. Using a large pair of scissors, cut ring around at 2-inch intervals, leaving inner edge intact. Turn each slice to lie flat on pan. Let rise until light and bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes. Frost while hot with sugar frosting.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with water.
Add drained pineapple and blueberries.
Let jell.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of Jell-O mixture.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla and mix well. Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans all over.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
Allow pie to completely cool before serving.
Serve with whipped cream or your favorite, if desired.

title: quick salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of water (hot).
Add buttermilk and pineapple; mix well.
Put in refrigerator to jell.
When jelled, add whipped Cool Whip, stirring well, and refrigerate for about 10 minutes.
This is very good.

title: caliente pickles
directions: Soak pickles overnight in 3/4 cup salt and 1 gallon of water. In a saucepan, boil 1 1/2 quarts vinegar, 3/4 cup salt, sugar, 2 1/2 quarts water and pickling spice (in a cloth).
In canning jars, put in dill weed or dill seed, garlic, mustard seed and cucumbers.
Pour liquid mixture into jars and seal.
Process 20 minutes.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and eggs; beat.
Add vanilla and baking powder.
Make a well, add the combined ingredients, knead and shape into 2 inch ovals.
Dip in milk and roll in sesame seed, place approximately 1 inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 15 minutes.
They are done when nicely brown.

title: broccoli and squash casserole
directions: Dice broccoli and slice squash.
Put into a large pot; steam vegetables for about 8 to 10 minutes, until tender but not soft! In a large casserole, layer squash, onion, broccoli, bacon, mushrooms and cheese.
Continue layers until you run out of ingredients.
Mix together the soup, eggs and milk.
Add flour to wet mixture.
Pour over vegetable casserole.
(I poke a few holes into the vegetable mix to allow the soup mixture to go all the way through!)
Make sure the vegetables are covered with the mixture. Bake, covered, at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover; bake about 10 to 15 more minutes to golden brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: norwegian flat bread
directions: Mix all together and add enough cold water to hold together like a pie crust.
Roll out very thin with grooved rolling pin and bake slowly on ungreased griddle or in a moderate oven, 325° to 350°.
Watch closely.
When it begins to get a light golden color, turn and bake on other side.
Let dry out completely before putting into a container.
Keep in a dry place.

title: sour cream devil's food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cocoa and soda with boiling water.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked fish special
directions: Place fillets in a greased baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Mix the remaining ingredients and cover the fillets with the mixture. Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: impossible peach pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour, then add the beaten eggs.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 buttered and floured pie pans. Bake at 350° until the custard is set, about 30 to 40 minutes. This makes 2 pies that will make their own crusts.

title: valentine's strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drain 1/4 cup juice from 1 small box frozen strawberries.
Reserve for glaze.
Add strawberries to previous mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: spaghetti with butter and eggs
directions: Boil noodles until tender. Drain some of the water, leaving 1-inch above noodles in pan. Add butter, parsley and eggs (scrambled) into noodle and water mixture.
Stir constantly over low heat until eggs are cooked. Salt to taste.
Let mixture stand for 15 minutes. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: "sour" salad dressing (italian)(zachary's favorite salad dressing)
directions: Mix together and pour over salad.

title: lemon frosting
directions: Blend all together thoroughly; spread on cake.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Wash lettuce; break into bite size pieces.
Fry bacon and onion until bacon is slightly crisp.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper to bacon and drippings.
Toss with lettuce and serve immediately. Makes 8 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over the oatmeal.
Let cool. Add the sugar, oil, brown sugar, eggs, flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger macaroni
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Brown meat with onion in large skillet; drain. Season with salt and pepper, if desired. Stir in undrained tomatoes, ketchup and pasta; heat through. Top with cheese. Garnish, if desired.

title: crab or shrimp mornay
directions: Melt butter; add flour, cornstarch and salt.
Stir until well blended.
While on heat, pour consomme in gradually until it comes to boil.
Add milk gradually.
Bring to boiling point.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Butter 8 shells or baking dish.
Cover bottom with fish.
Cover with sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Put dish or shells in pan under broiler to brown.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato pudding(serves 20)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in eggs, spice, salt and cream. Fold in greased sweet potato.
Pour into buttered shallow 2 to 3-quart baking dish.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: crickets
directions: Combine all ingredients, except almonds and raisins, and blend well with a mixer, then stir in almonds and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 54 to 60 cookies.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery. Add rest of the ingredients. Mix and bake in oven 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put one teaspoon portions of dough on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until brown (approximately 10 to 12 minutes).

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: In medium mixing bowl, soften oleo; add sugar, syrup and salt. On full power, microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir; microwave for 2 more minutes.
Take out and add soda and vanilla.
Have popped corn in brown paper sack and pour caramel over, stirring well. Put in on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir and repeat 3 more times for total of 4 1/2 minutes.

title: easy skillet chicken
directions: Place 2 tablespoons chicken broth and onion in a large skillet and cook over medium heat about 5 minutes or until onion softens. Add the peppers and celery; cook an additional 5 minutes or until vegetables begin to color.
Add chicken, remaining vegetables and broth.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon each Italian seasoning and paprika.
Cook slowly over low heat without covering for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Add remaining Italian seasoning, paprika and pepper.
Continue to cook for 20 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: vegetable stock
directions: This stock is fat-free and light in flavor.
Use as a base for your soups and homemade risotto.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients well and fry in small amount of butter or margarine (not oil).

title: goody cake
directions: Spread pie filling in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange chunk pineapple over pie filling.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Cover with melted butter, then sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: festive fudge
directions: Mix in a heavy 2-quart saucepan the sugar, milk, marshmallows, margarine and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil (mixture will be bubbling all over the top).
Boil and stir 5 additional minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in until completely melted the chocolate pieces, then add nuts and vanilla. Spread into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into 30 pieces.

title: grilled quail
directions: Marinate quail in Italian dressing for 3 to 4 hours.
Wrap in bacon.
Secure with a toothpick.
Cook over medium fire until bacon is done (20 minutes).

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix sugar, oil, syrup and egg in a bowl.
In another bowl, stir using spoon flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger.
Now combine both mixtures.
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: This mixture makes enough for a half dozen chickens or thick steaks.
Rub meat well with salt and pepper.
Daub on the mixture with a mop made by wrapping a rag around a stick.
Baste almost continually as the meat is turned.
Use the surplus to pour over the meat for gravy.
Barbecue slow and easy.
Cook the meat only over live coals burned down to where they are covered with a layer of white ash.

title: 3 cup christmas bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil and milk.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: caramels
directions: Boil all together except the nuts and 1 cup cream.
Boil 30 minutes.
Add second cup of cream.
Boil to a firm ball stage (248°).
Add nuts.
Pour without stirring into well buttered pan. When cool, cut into squares.

title: homemade mints
directions: Gradually add powdered sugar to cream cheese, mixing thoroughly during the process, by hand.
Add flavoring and coloring.
For best results, work into firm ball and wrap with plastic wrap.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Use mold to press out shapes, if desired.

title: rebel chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain well; mix all ingredients together in large pot and cook over medium to low heat approximately 1 hour.

title: full meal stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave at High for 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Combine soup and milk; stir in rice, chicken, cheese, chopped pepper and celery.
Divide into peppers. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple cider
directions: Pour apple juice into a crock-pot; add cinnamon sticks. Turn on high for approximately 1 hour.

title: hot diggity dogs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slit hot dogs lengthwise.
Insert strip of cheese.
Place hot dogs carefully and diagonally on crescent rolls.
Wrap around hot dog.
Place on cookie sheet and bake until rolls are golden brown, 13 to 15 minutes.

title: company tuna casserole
directions: Combine 1/2 can noodles with remaining ingredients in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle on noodles.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: mom's pecan tarts
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Press into muffin pans.
Mix sugar, eggs, salt, margarine and vanilla. Pour into mini pie shells.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer Swiss cheese slices over the chicken.
Mix 1 can of water with soup.
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Melt 1/2 stick of margarine and mix in 2 cups of the stuffing.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt.
Stir in chocolate syrup, flour and vanilla. Add nuts and blend well.
Turn into greased and lightly floured 8-inch square micro-safe pan or dish.
Microwave at High for 3 minutes.
Let rest 3 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Blend sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Stir in molasses.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well.
Spread in a well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or applesauce.
Yields 8 to 10.

title: mom's macaroni cheese and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box and drain.
Grate cheese.
Pour evaporated milk, margarine and macaroni into pan and add cheese.
After cheese melts, add tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
For added flavor, add bacon, ham or peas.

title: sheath cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Mix and bring to a boil oleo, Wesson oil, water and cocoa.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake at 375° in 9 x 13-inch pan, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave barbecue chicken
directions: Combine barbecue sauce and parsley in small mixing bowl.
Mix well and set aside.
Brush both sides of chicken with sauce. Place skin side up and thick edges towards outside of 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Microwave 18 to 23 minutes on High or until meat cut towards bone is not pink.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: *Can be replaced with 16 ounces ready to serve cream of mushroom soup.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Top with pie filling or serve without.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Wipe spareribs and lay in roasting pan.
Blend other ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover last 30 minutes.
Turn and baste meat frequently.

title: bread cinnamon roll
directions: Remove crusts from bread and roll out flat with rolling pin. Mix together cheese, egg yolk, 1/8 cup sugar and vanilla.
Spread 1 teaspoon on each slice and roll up.
Melt butter and roll breads in it, then a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place seam side down on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut in half.
Serve warm or cold.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine and drain first 6 ingredients; put in large bowl. Combine and mix well sugar, oil, vinegar, pepper and salt.
Pour over mixed ingredients.
Cover tightly; refrigerate.
Flavor improves after 2 to 3 days.
Makes about 12 servings.
Can be halved or doubled.
(I do not use either the black pepper or the salt.)

title: holiday sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

In large mixing bowl, beat oil and sugar on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs and vanilla and beat until light in texture. Reduce speed and add flour, baking powder and salt Mix on low speed until ingredients incorporate. Cover and refrigerate dough until firm, at least 30 minutes.

title: country succotash
directions: Combine beans and corn in saucepan with their liquid, with a generous lump of butter and salt and pepper.
Let simmer over medium-low heat until liquid reduces.
Serves six.

title: jerk sauce
directions: In a large bowl combine the spices and sugar (first 9 ingredients).
Combine the liquid ingredients together and using a wire whisk, slowly add to the bowl of spices.
Add the Scotch Bonnet and onions and mix well.
Pour into a wide mouth jar or container with a lid and let set over night in the refrigerator so the flavors blend.
Shake well before using.
Can be used as a marinade for Chicken, Beef or Pork,
coat and let set for at least 1 hour before cooking.
Can be cooked any style.
Also makes a great dipping sauce.
It's really good and quite easy.

title: becca's vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Let stand for 24 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle them on top.
Bake in buttered casserole dish for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: old-fashioned butter cookies
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar.
Add the milk, egg and vanilla. Sift the flour, salt and baking powder.
Blend in the dry ingredients.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Divide into thirds.
Roll on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut out and sprinkle with plain or colored sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: oriental spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until done.
Set aside.
In covered skillet, brown beef and pork.
Add celery and onions; cook 30 minutes.
Add soups, vegetables and mushrooms.
Adjust seasonings.
Cook 10 minutes.
Layer spaghetti and meat mixture in casserole, 2 layers each.
Cover with grated cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Knead dough with powdered sugar; press in molds.
Dip in granulated sugar.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in bowl.
Shake biscuit quarters in mixture. Drop into greased Bundt pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: "better than sex" cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Cool slightly and prick surface with a clean pencil or round spoon handle.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake; then pour caramel topping over cake.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Frost cake with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put into casserole.

title: one-eyed connaly french toast with egg
directions: Preheat griddle (nonstick or a little oil).
Cut hole in center of bread slice with small glass or biscuit cutter.
Beat one egg and mix in sugar, milk and vanilla.
Dip bread into egg mixture and place on hot griddle.
After 1 minute, place an egg (minus shell) into hole in bread.
Turn over when bottom of egg turns white.

title: instant spice tea
directions: Mix thoroughly and use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to a cup of hot water.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter, flour, salt and vanilla until fluffy. Then add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each one.
Add milk. Bake in 350° oven until knife comes out clean.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add all the ingredients.
Mix with mayonnaise to taste.
Cut up the crabmeat into chunks.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 8 ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture; turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Remove chicken from marinade; coat each piece with crumbs.
Arrange on a shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes, or until juice runs clear.
Yields 8 servings.

title: ann's lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna noodles according to package.
Drain and rinse noodles in cold water.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, add 1/4 cup spaghetti sauce.
Spread in bottom.
Add the following layers: noodles, sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese in order. Continue this pattern; top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese with vegetables
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions for about 10 minutes. Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in a medium saucepan.
Remove the pan from the heat; stir in the flour until well blended.
Stir in the vegetable stock or water and milk; place the pan back over medium heat.
Stir the mixture until it comes to a boil and thickens. Reduce heat to low.
Stir in cheeses, parsley, basil and spices. Continue stirring until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat; set aside.
In a skillet over medium heat, melt remaining margarine. Stir in broccoli, pepper, mushrooms and green onion.
Keep stirring until vegetables are soft.
When pasta is done, drain well.
Toss with the vegetables and the cheese sauce.
Serve hot.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients like pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then mix remaining ingredients together and spread over crust when cool and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: walnut crunch pumpkin pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Mix walnuts and brown sugar in small bowl.
Place 3/4 cup in bottom of pie shell.
Reserve remaining mixture for topping. Combine egg, pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, salt and evaporated milk in bowl; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.

title: copper carrots
directions: Pour mixture over drained, warm carrots. Cool at room temperature. Store in refrigerator.
Keeps for several weeks.

title: beef in a crockpot
directions: Combine last five ingredients and pour over meat.
Cook on low all day.
Remove roast and thicken broth.
Serve over noodles.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: In blender, place sugar, butter and dry milk.
Add boiling water.
Beat until smooth.
Equals the same as regular 14 ounce can of condensed milk.

title: donald's shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix well and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: lychee-longan-mandarin nectar
directions: Puree each fruit with its packing syrup. Combine fruit purees in a container, refrigerate a minimum of 2 hours.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: cocktail franks
directions: In
saucepan,
over medium heat, melt grape jelly.
Add mustard.
Add franks and let simmer until heated through.
Can be done in electric frypan right at table to keep hot.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate 2 hours. Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: heavenly jello
directions: Blend all 3 milks together (in blender).
Boil water, then add gelatine; stir until dissolved.
Add gelatine mix to the blender. Blend thoroughly.
Drain juice from cocktail fruit.
In a glass container (rectangular dish), layer the fruit cocktail.
Then take the mixed milk and pour over fruit cocktail.
Refrigerate for about 3 to 4 hours or until firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients; add oil and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add carrots, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes.

title: greenhouse zucchini nut bread(from costello's greenhouse restaurant)
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in two greased and floured loaf pans.

title: nuts & bolts party mix
directions: Mix oil, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and seasoned salt. Pour over cereal and mix with wooden spoon.
Bake at 250 degrees for 2 hours, turning mix every 15 minutes.

title: creamy broccoli au gratin soup
directions: Cook onion and butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Add water, rice and contents of seasoning packet.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Combine flour and dry mustard in a small bowl.
Gradually add about 1/2 cup of the broth, stirring until smooth.
Stir remaining broth, flour mixture and milk into rice mixture.
Heat to a simmer, stirring occasionally. Continue simmering until slightly thickened.
Stir in cheese. Sprinkle with green onions, if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, syrup and flour together.
Put pecans in unbaked pastry shell (9-inch).
Pour in ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add salt, syrup, sugar and margarine.
Place pecans in 9-inch unbaked pie shell and pour mixture over them.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until firm.

title: chi-cho
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread mixture onto tortillas. Roll. Slice and enjoy.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix the last 4 ingredients to form crumbs.
Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Beat 4 to 5 minutes after adding rest.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured tube pan, then 1/2 of crumbs, then rest of batter and rest of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: new potatoes with onion-dijon dressing
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Shake until blended; set aside.
Cook potatoes.
Pour dressing on potatoes and sprinkle with onions and parsley.
Serve warm or cold.
Very good!

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Mix dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
You may desire more coloring than an ounce.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 90 minutes.

title: custard bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Pour milk over bread cubes.
Add salt and
sugar.
Beat
eggs; add to bread mixture with butter and vanilla,
mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Set casserole in a pan with hot water within 1 inch of top.
Bake
50 to 60 minutes, or until knife inserted near rim comes out clean. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate until time to serve.

title: barbecue spareribs(baked in foil)
directions: Use big, flat pan.
Use enough foil to wrap completely and tightly around the ribs.
Season ribs with salt and Creole-Cajun seasoning.
Spread with bottled barbecue sauce, topped with thin slices of onion, then seal tightly in foil.
Bake at 325° about 3 hours, until meat is tender and falling off bone.
Good and easy.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix sugar, salt and dry cocoa; add part of water to make a paste, then remainder of water.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes. Pour at once into jar and when cool, place in refrigerator.

title: cherry cheese delight
directions: Put broken pieces of cake in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Mix pudding, milk and cheese together.
Pour over cake.
Place in refrigerator and let set.
Spoon cherry mix over it and serve with Cool Whip.

title: kahlua
directions: Stir sugar and water until sugar dissolves and it boils.
Add coffee; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Add brandy.
Pour into dark bottles over vanilla beans (2 beans per decanter).
Age at least 3 months.
Proof doubles every 6 months.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: zahtar pizza(thyme pizza)
directions: Add sufficient oil to zahtar to make a thin paste.
Make 4 inch circular patties out of the dough.
Cover and let rest 15-20 mins.
Spread mixture over dough patties.
Bake 470° for 10 mins. This will make 1 dozen 4 inch patties.

title: holiday nut loaf
directions: Drain and add maraschino cherries.
Stir to coat nuts and fruit with flour mixture.
Beat eggs and add vanilla.
Mix well into flour and fruit mixture.
Easiest to mix with hands in a big container.

title: pie crust(single 9-inch)
directions: In a 2 cup measuring cup, mix ingredients.
Roll between wax paper.
For single baked crust, bake 8 to 10 minutes at 475°.

title: snickers cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Then mix next 5 ingredients together.
Wrap 1 tablespoon of dough around the bite size Snicker. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Pound into meat.
In large skillet, brown meat on both sides in shortening.
Top with onion and tomatoes; cover and cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add green pepper; cook 15 minutes more.
Skim off excess fat.
Thicken juice, if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy shepherd's pie
directions: Fry ground beef; drain off all fat.
Put in bottom of casserole dish that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Add creamed corn and top with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbling hot.
Serve with a tossed salad.

title: chocolate-covered peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and white chocolate in a double boiler pan until smooth.
Add peanuts and coat well with chocolate. Spoon onto wax paper.
Cluster; size can vary.
Allow to harden or place in refrigerator for faster hardening.
Place in glass jar or tin can.

title: bread pudding
directions: Lightly butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Blend eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and spices.
While stirring, add milk slowly.
Add bread and fruit and mix well.
Pour into baking dish and dot with butter.
Place dish in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: heavenly rolled round roast
directions: Pound the steaks until thin.
Rub in salt, pepper and plenty of paprika.
Overlap the steaks, making 1 large steak.
Spread the meat with a layer of mushrooms and blanket them with the onions. Cut pimentos in half and lay over the onions.
Cover with fine bread crumbs.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Press into 9-inch pie plate.

title: chocolate cooler cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: blueberry spice cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° in greased and floured pan until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Saute ham and green onions in 3 tablespoons butter in a large skillet until onion is tender.
Add eggs and cook over medium-high heat, stirring to form large, soft curds.
When eggs are set, stir in mushrooms and Cheese Sauce.
Spoon eggs into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine 1/4 cup melted butter and crumbs, mixing well.
Spread evenly over egg mixture. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and chill casserole overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: candied cranberries
directions: Wash cranberries and spread over the bottom of a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Chill before serving.

title: five-minute fruit salad
directions: Thoroughly drain fruits, saving 1 cup juice.
Mix fruits, juice, lemon juice and pudding.
Mix together.
Stir well.
Chill. Just before serving, slice the bananas into it and stir well again.

title: saucy tomato pork chops
directions: Combine flour, thyme and coat chops.
In skillet, cook chops in hot oil 10 minutes on one side, then turn over and cook other side until brown.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, water and onion and return chops to skillet and cook 10 minutes or until pink is out.

title: broccoli souffle(microwave)
directions: Place broccoli in vented box on paper plate.
Microwave on 100% power for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine eggs and flour in medium mixing bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients and broccoli.
Pour into 1-quart casserole or souffle dish.
Microwave at 50% power for 17 to 22 minutes or until almost set in center (200°).
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan pie(lp)
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and melted oleo. Add beaten eggs and vanilla, mixing well.

Add pecans to syrup mixture. Mix well. Pour into pie shells and bake at 375° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes. Remove from oven and place a sheet of wax paper over top until cool.

title: filleted catfish with almonds
directions: Soak catfish fillets in milk for 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper. Dip in flour.
Back in milk and then back in flour a second time. Heat margarine in an iron skillet.
Put fillets in margarine and brown quickly on each side.
Turn heat to low and add almonds along side of fish until lightly browned.
Put almonds on top of fish and cook about 10 minutes.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put salt on all vegetables, mix and let stand until some liquid forms, then drain off.
Mix sugar and vinegar and a little celery seed.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Let stand a while, then mix again.
Put in covered dishes or jars and store in refrigerator.
Will keep several months.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix
together
vinegar,
sugar	and salt.
Pour mixture over sliced vegetables.	This will keep six weeks in refrigerator in a covered container.

title: gorp
directions: Mix all the ingredients together for a tasty snack.
Store in an airtight container.

title: oklahoma noodles
directions: Brown meat and drain.
While meat is cooking, slice green peppers into large slices (not chopped).
Brown in a small amount of olive oil until tender, but still firm.
Add the can of tomatoes (undrained) and the meat.
Add about 1/4 teaspoon pepper, 1/8 teaspoon red pepper, 1 tablespoon sugar and minced garlic. Tabasco can also be added to taste.
Other spices can be added as desired.
When all ingredients are added, simmer for 1/2 hour, until flavors blend.
Cook noodles only until firm and add to mixture.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Add hot water to cranberry sauce.
Cream oleo and sugar together.
Add eggs and all other ingredients.
Mix.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
This makes one regular loaf pan or 2 small ones.

title: pralines
directions: Mix sugar, buttermilk, butter, soda and salt in a large pot. Cook over medium heat to "soft ball stage".
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts and beat to glaze stage and drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool before removing.

title: cheese ball
directions: Melt Velveeta in microwave.
Add cream cheese.
Mix well. Chill.
Form into 2 balls, then roll in chili powder.
Serve with any dip crackers.
Can add picante sauce, if desired.

title: egg rolls
directions: Grind all vegetables in food processor.
Boil noodles; add to vegetables.
Brown sausage; add to mixture.
Put about 2 tablespoons of mixture into each skin; fold all corners in and roll up, sealing last corner with beaten egg.
Deep fry when ready to use.
Makes 40 to 45 egg rolls.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes in water.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients together.
Fold broccoli into this mixture and pour into casserole dish.
Spread bread or cracker crumbs on top (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix oil, buttermilk, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Add 4 cups of flour and mix well.
Add yeast (in warm water) and rest of flour.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Do not let rise before baking.
Use dough as needed.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Place half of tomatoes in baking pan (10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch).
Top each half with onion, cheese and crumbs; repeat.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into yolks; return to hot mixture and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter, coconut and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour into baked pastry shell.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in a covered dish.
May be prepared a day ahead of time and stored in refrigerator until ready to bake.
If you do this, cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Also delicious even when reheated.

title: date pecan balls
directions: Combine butter and sugar; add vanilla.
Add flour and mix. Add pecans and dates.
Roll teaspoonfuls of dough into balls. Refrigerate balls 1 1/2 hours.
Bake on greased cookie sheet approximately 20 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar after cookies have cooled.
Sprinkle with sugar again.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Blend all together and then add eggs, one at a time, when beating.
Pour half of batter in pan and sprinkle 2 tablespoons of brown sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon and nuts on it.
Then add rest of batter.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Put in a 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Mix together milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper.
Beat one minute.
