Pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: ginger garlic broccoli(from china)
directions: Cut off broccoli flowerets and slash their stems; peel and thinly slice stalks.
Heat a wok or wide frying pan over high heat.
Add oil.
Add garlic and ginger and stir once; then add broccoli and stir-fry for one minute.
Add water; cover and cook until the broccoli is tender-crisp (3 to 4 minutes).
Asparagus may be substituted for broccoli.

title: pineapple reuben salad
directions: Spread bread with butter.
Cut into 1/2-inch squares.
Bake in a slow oven (300°) for 20 to 25 minutes, until dry and crisp. Turn pineapple into wire strainer and drain well.
Rinse and drain sauerkraut.
Place lettuce in a large bowl.
Top with pineapple, sauerkraut, corned beef, cheese and croutons.
Stir caraway seed into dressing.

title: lunch for a bunch
directions: Prepare roll mix according to package directions.
When ready to shape, on a well floured surface, knead the dough about 10 times.
Roll dough to form rectangles about 12 x 18 inches.
Mix 1 teaspoon dressing mix with butter; spread on dough.
Sprinkle on cheese and place ham slices on cheese.
Use the longer side and roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Pinch the raw edges into the dough and form a big circle (zero) on a greased pizza pan.
Pinch ends together.
Cover; let rise until double in size (about 45 to 60 minutes).
Slit top using kitchen shears every 3 inches.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, or until top is golden brown. Cool on rack completely.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Fry sausage; drain and cool.
Put bread flat in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle on sausage.
Beat eggs; add milk and pour over all.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake when needed in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, butter, 1/2 cup flour, salt and cinnamon for topping.
Sift remaining flour and soda together.
Cream egg, shortening and remaining sugar.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle with topping. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with curry powder until tender; before you put the chicken in, salt and pepper the water to taste.
When done, remove and cut chicken off bones into chunks or small pieces.
Boil broccoli in same water until tender.
In a large bowl, mix chicken, both soups, mayo and broccoli together, then stir in 1 cup of cornbread stuffing and 1 cup of cheese.
Mix well, then put in baking dish and top with a little more cheese.
Top with 1 cup cornbread stuffing.
Pour melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: marion's bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Put in pot and cover with water.

Let soak for 8 hours; drain and add chicken broth, onion, carrots, celery, garlic, parsley, basil, oregano, salt, pepper and spinach. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender.

title: jordan marsh's big blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease tins.
Cream butter well, then add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well. Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Fold in all the blueberries at once.
Fill to the top; sprinkle with the reserved sugar.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 1/2 hour in pan.

title: a. p. cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato yams
directions: Boil sweet potatoes for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool and peel; slice and place in greased baking dish.

title: cheesy carrot top chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts, cut in half, in greased baking dish. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.

title: uncle billy's bread pudding
directions: Stir all ingredients (except butter) real good.
Let soak for 10 minutes.
Melt 1/4 stick butter in a casserole dish; then pour in mixture.
Bake at 450° for 35 minutes.
Let cool and serve. Delicious!

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all the filling ingredients together thoroughly (first 8 items).
Divide filling and spread evenly over tortillas.
Roll up tortillas.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap, twisting ends. Refrigerate for several hours.
Unwrap.
Cut in slices 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Serve with salsa.

title: chocolate icebox cake
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add water and blend.
Remove from fire and add egg yolk, beating vigorously until blended.
Add sugar and walnuts.
Blend.
Fold in egg white and cream.
Line mold or loaf pan with ladyfingers or pieces of plain angel food cake.
Pour in chocolate mix; cover with ladyfingers and chill in refrigerator 12 to 24 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; season to your taste.
Put in 8 x 8
casserole dish; spread cheese sauce on top of potatoes.	Bake in oven at 350° or 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until hot.

title: frosted cake drops
directions: Cream butter well with powdered sugar, beating in eggs 2 at a time.
Add flour and flavoring.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can be served plain or with fruit.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter well. Add sugar gradually and cream well. Add eggs (room temperature), one at a time. Add cream, then flour gradually. Add flavoring.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 30 minutes, then at 275° for 1 hour or until done.

title: custard pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs, then add sugar, salt and vanilla. Gradually stir in scalded milk. Pour into pastry shell and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake for an hour or until custard is set in the middle.

title: salsa bean dip
directions: Mix together.
Heat in a double boiler.
Serve hot with chips.

title: diabetic date nut cake
directions: Cream margarine, sweetener, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and beat.
Add applesauce, dates and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for one hour.

title: fudge
directions: Heat the chocolate chips, milk, vanilla and salt in heavy saucepan until melted, then add peanut butter chips or butterscotch chips just until melted.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours before cutting.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crisp lemon thins
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add the brown sugar, creaming well. Blend in 1 unbeaten egg and 3/4 cup flour.

Mix thoroughly. Stir in the almonds, oats, lemon rind and lemon extract. Drop by teaspoonfuls at least 3-inches apart onto greased baking sheet. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes until edges are golden brown.
Remove from sheet immediately.

title: stuffed zucchini boats
directions: Cut end off zucchini and cut lengthwise in half to make 8 boats.
Hollow out inside of zucchini in a canoe fashion, leaving 1/4-inch flesh on boat.
Heat water to boiling; salt lightly. Blanch boats in water for 3 to 4 minutes until flesh is tender. Lift out gently; drain upside down on paper towels.
Melt margarine in medium pan.
Saute garlic, onion, celery, carrots and red bell pepper until tender.
Mix sauteed vegetables, bread cubes, chicken broth, marjoram, sweet basil, thyme, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup of the Parmesan cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place zucchini boats in lightly oiled shallow baking pan.
Fill boats with stuffing mix.
Sprinkle tops with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is browned.
Makes 8 servings.

title: salmon log or ball
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing skin and bones.
Combine salmon with next 7 ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours.
Shape into log or ball.
Roll salmon mixture into combination of nuts and parsley.
Chill well.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheese cake
directions: Sprinkle crushed wafers in bottom of spring-form pan.
Mix ingredients, folding in chocolate chips.
Slowly pour over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Contains 220 calories per serving.
There are 12 servings per cake and 7 grams of fat.

title: hearty bacon-potato chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon over medium heat.
Add potatoes and onions after bacon is cooked.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients; continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until heated through (10 to 12 minutes).
Makes 6 servings.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Fold pudding into softened Cool Whip.
Add pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.
Refrigerate for an hour.

title: creole rice pilaf
directions: Slice mushrooms into a skillet.
Add onion, green pepper, parsley, tomatoes, tomato paste, oil, butter, salt and pepper. Place on low heat.
In about 10 minutes, add the rice and the water.
Cook for 20 minutes in all.
Put a lid on the skillet. Add water if the mixture becomes too dry.
All the liquid should be completely absorbed when the rice is tender.
Serves 4.

title: aunt will's chinese salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: washington chowder
directions: Saute onions and potatoes.
Add water and cook until done. Add rest of ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: carrots and brussels sprouts with lemon butter(serves 6)
directions: Cook carrots and Brussels sprouts together in boiling, salted water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan with lemon peel and juice, caraway seed and garlic.
Add cooked vegetables and heat.
Contains 140 calories per serving.

title: reese's cake
directions: Bake cake as directions say.
When cooled, put 1 layer on plate and spread with peanut butter only on top, not on sides.
Do same thing with next layer.
When you place one layer on top of the other, spread peanut butter on top.
Now use chocolate icing. Spread over entire cake and break up Reese's and place over various parts of the outside of the cake.

title: mississippi rice with chicken
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender; remove from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Combine onion soup mix, mushroom soup and pimento.
Alternate layers of rice, chicken and soup mix in a casserole, ending with mushroom soup mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts and cooks to a golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: el dorado casserole
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients.
Crumble 1 bag tortilla chips and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add meat mixture for the next layer. Mix last four ingredients and spread over meat layer.
Top with 2 cups of shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: southern pralines
directions: Lightly butter a sheet of aluminum foil.
Combine sugars, cream and salt in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to 228° on candy thermometer (or until mixture spins a thread about 2 inches long when dropped from a spoon)
Stir in butter and pecans.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, to 236° (or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball which flattens when removed from water)
Remove form heat; cool 5 minutes.
Beat mixture with wooden spoon until slightly thickened and candy just coats nuts but does not lose its gloss.
Drop candy by large spoonfuls onto buttered foil.
Yield: 1-1/2 dozen candies.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, sour cream, onions, soup, cheese and half of butter.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour other half of butter over cornflakes and spread over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta shells until tender.
Drain.
Cool.
Mix cheeses, eggs and spices.
Stuff shells.
Place in baking dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Use Crisco to grease tube pan well and set aside.

title: quickie peach cobbler
directions: Cut 1/2 stick of margarine in bottom of large Pyrex bowl or long oblong cake pan.
Heat peaches to boiling point.
Mix sugar, flour and buttermilk together.
Pour fruit in Pyrex dish and then pour flour, sugar and buttermilk over peaches.
Cut 1/2 stick margarine over peaches and then sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Bake in 350° oven until brown, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cilantro potatoes
directions: Wash and bake potatoes in oven at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
While potatoes are baking, combine the remainder of the ingredients and toss it lightly in a bowl.
When potatoes are done, remove from the oven and let them cool to the touch.
Cut the potatoes in half lengthwise and fluff with a fork.
Top each potato with approximately 1/4 of the topping mixture.
Return to oven or microwave just long enough to melt cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chop apples, oranges and peaches into small bite sizes.
Take all of the fruit and put into a large bowl.
Then add the coconut and pecans.
When all is mixed, add sugar and stir around.
Then add the Cool Whip.
Makes a large bowl.

title: lowfat skillet lasagna
directions: Combine the chicken and pasta sauce in a skillet.
I use an electric skillet for the lasagna.
Heat thoroughly.
Stir in cottage cheese, Parmesan and noodles.
Simmer for about 5 minutes. Sprinkle both kinds of mozzarella cheese over the top.
Remove from heat and cover for about 3 minutes.
Heat from the lasagna will melt the cheese.
If you get 7 servings, the fat gram count per serving is less than 2 grams.

title: ice cream pudding
directions: Roll out crackers with a rolling pin on a sheet of Reynold's Wrap, then mix by hand with softened margarine.
Save 3/4 cup for dessert topping.
Spread in bottom of cake pan and pat down.
Mix together ice cream, vanilla pudding and milk, then layer it in pan on top of crackers.
Mix Dream Whip and spread on top of pudding mixture.
Sprinkle the leftover 3/4 cup crackers on the top and enjoy!

title: quick tortonis
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the ice cream, whipped topping and 1/4 teaspoon almond extract.
Spoon mixture into 6 fluted paper baking cups.
Place cups in cupcake pan cups.
Combine crumbs, sugar and 1/4 teaspoon almond extract; mix well.
Spoon crumbs on top of tortoni mixture.
Freeze until firm.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Brown chopped meat and onion in oil.
Drain.
Add chili sauce, paprika, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer until thick.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes in a greased pan or dish.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine in a bowl, chicken, eggs, mushrooms, peas, carrots, soup and gravy.
Fill the pie shell with the meat filling and cover with a baked pie top.
Bake until the filling is thoroughly heated and the top is a light golden brown.

title: steak champignon
directions: In 8-inch nonstick skillet, heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot; add mushrooms and saute until browned. Reduce heat to low; add wine and cook, stirring frequently, for 2 minutes, stirring constantly, until heated.
Remove skillet from heat; set aside and keep sauce warm.
On rack in broiling pan, broil steaks, turning once, until done to taste.
Remove steaks to serving platter; pour sauce over steaks or transfer sauce to gravy boat and serve with steaks.
Makes 2 servings.
Contains 353 calories and 170 mg sodium.

title: no crust peach pie
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and spices.
Cut in oleo to make fine crumbs.
Press 1 cup mixture into bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pie pan.
Mix fruit with 1/2 cup sugar and lemon rind. Spoon over crumbs in pan.
Use remaining crumbs to cover top of peaches in pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: fudge topped peanut butter pie
directions: Whisk together pudding mix, sour cream and milk in medium bowl; set aside. Place 1 1/2 cups peanut butter chips and oil in microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on HIGH 45 seconds or until smooth. Using hand mixer, gradually add to pudding mixture; spread evenly into crust. Spread chocolate fudge topping over pie; cover and refrigerate 3 hours. Prior to serving, top with remaining peanut butter chips. Servings: 8.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Make a well and add liquids.
Do not use a mixer.
Add apples and nuts; stir gently.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes for small loaf.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt oleo and add chocolate.
Beat eggs and add sugar, flour and salt.
Combine with chocolate.
Pour into pie plate and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with ice cream.

title: almond chicken(crock-pot)
directions: Pour chicken broth into crock-pot.
Cover; put on high.
Brown meat and vegetables.
In skillet, put butter, bacon and chicken. Brown on all sides.
Remove chicken and bacon to crock-pot. Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in skillet until slightly limp.
Put vegetables in crock-pot with soy sauce.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour.
Serve over hot rice.
Garnish with toasted almonds.
Serves 4.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Make batter and add to butter.
Spread fruit on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream.
Use any fruit (apples, cherries, etc.).

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a shallow greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until roast appears firm.
Serves 4.

title: artichoke heart dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until brown on edges.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: bora bora
directions: Fill a 22-ounce brandy snifter with crushed ice and a lime squeeze.
Add all ingredients.
Stir and garnish with pineapple, orange slice and a cherry.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Put milk, sugar, cocoa and butter in saucepan.
Bring to rolling boil; boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Set aside and blend oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and place in a butter baking dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan with butter.
Butter top of six slices of bread and place in bottom of pan.
Beat 6 eggs together and mix with milk to equal a quarter (4 cups).
Place cheese slices or shredded cheese on bread slices.
Cover with meat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pink champagne salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in strawberries, bananas, whipped topping and pineapple.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.
Keeps in freezer 1 week to 10 days.

title: pork chops, kraut and potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops.
Boil potatoes.
Place browned pork chops, kraut and potatoes in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: basic cream sauce
directions: Melt butter and add 3/4 cup milk.
Mix cornstarch in cup with remaining 1/4 cup milk.
Then add to other milk in saucepan; stirring constantly, heat until mixture just starts to boil and turn heat off.
Can add Swiss, Cheddar or Velveeta cheese to make a cheese sauce.
Pour over noodles, potatoes or chopped broccoli.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with chicken.
Layer the Veg-All, then eggs (sliced) over chicken.
Combine the broth and soup and pour over the layers, them mix the flour, milk and oleo and pour over all.
Bake at 350° until top crust is brown.

title: mini-ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Flake biscuits apart and place in a mini muffin pan, use a tart shaper or thumb to press down each biscuit. Then in a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients and spoon into each biscuit. Bake until golden brown.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Combine all; dip shrimp and fry.
Very light batter.

title: cornstarch-based paint
directions: Mix cornstarch with cold water to make a smooth thick paste. Stir in boiling water to a desired consistency.
The mixture should immediately become thick, lose its white appearance and turn fairly clear.
Spoon the mixture into paint cups or jars. Add liquid tempera and stir.

title: minestrone hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Combine all and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: heavenly cake
directions: Bake and cool.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sour cream biscuits(firmer texture, great with ham or sausage.)
directions: *The consistency of sour cream varies slightly, so begin with about 2 tablespoons less than 1 cup.
If dough is stiff, add remaining sour cream.

title: cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and set aside.
Whip until stiff.
Add jello and pineapple; stir well.
Then add nuts, marshmallows and grated cheese.
Mix well and chill overnight.

title: scampi
directions: Clean, wash and dry fish.
In a saute pan, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil; saute garlic over a medium heat, being careful not to burn.
Add basil, oregano and mint; lower heat and saute 2 minutes. Add lemon juice and remove from heat.
In a separate pan, saute fish with remaining olive oil for approximately 3 minutes.
Add wine; heat 1 minute.
Add sauteed spices and cook 3 minutes over medium heat.
Serve with rice or pasta immediately.
If you use nonstick cookware, you can substitute water for the oil.

title: baked beans with hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger with bacon and onion.
Drain well.
Combine with other ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 325 degrees for at least 1 hour (the longer the better).

title: hot chocolate
directions: Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
To make hot chocolate, add 3 to 4 teaspoons of mixture to cup of hot water.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Combine flour and salt in a bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Sprinkle on water 1 tablespoon at a time, tossing with fork until pastry holds together.
Shape into balls; flatten into disk.
Wrap and refrigerate 1 hour.
Make topping.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar, egg and extract. Combine dry ingredients. Add alternately with milk to first mixture. Chill dough. Roll out 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick on floured board. Cut into desired shapes. With fork, beat egg white with a little water, lightly; brush on top of cookie. Sprinkle with sugar (colored or white). Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix well; pat firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes in 375° oven.
Cool.

title: dawn's microwave fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Add Carnation milk and powdered sugar. Microwave for 5 minutes on High, stirring twice.
Add chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.

title: alice perry's carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil to mixture and beat at low speed for 1 minute.
Add grated carrots, nuts and spread in greased oblong pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, or until cake tests done with toothpick.
When cool, spread with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Frost layers, sides and top.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Make sure fillets are thin and wide. Dip each fillet in beaten eggs. Coat both sides with bread crumbs.
Lay fillets on flat cookie sheet.
Place on each fillet, 2 slices of ham and 2 slices of Swiss cheese. Roll fillet from one corner.
Attach with toothpicks. Place in baking pan. Top with 2 to 3 tablespoons Prego. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream cheese peas(kids recipe #4)
directions: Heat peas until warm.
Add butter and cubed Velveeta.
Simmer on low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in sugar.
In a separate bowl or glass, whisk flour and milk until smooth.
Pour into peas. They will thicken very quickly.
They are good!

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into 6 patties.
Fry in small amount of cooking oil until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings (145 calories, 7 g fat).

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Pour pineapple in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top of pineapple.
Melt butter and pour over cheese.
Mix pineapple juice, sugar and flour and pour over pineapple mixture.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon torte
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in two 9-inch layer cake pans.
Cool completely.
Slice each layer into 2 layers, 4 in all.

title: oven fried catfish in cornmeal
directions: Preheat oven to top setting, 475° or 500° for five minutes. Meanwhile, combine fish fillets with mayonnaise in a plastic bag and shake to coat fish evenly. Combine cornmeal with remaining seasonings on a sheet of waxed paper or a shallow plate. Roll the coated fillets in the cornmeal, coating evenly. Arrange in a single layer on a wire grid in a shallow pan (spray both with cooking spray). Bake uncovered 9 to 10 minutes, until golden and crusty.

title: a crock of spinach
directions: Fill deep fryer or skillet 2 inches with oil; heat to 375°. Combine milk and egg in a bowl.
Stir together dry ingredients in a separate bowl and then add to egg mixture; blend well.
Fold in zucchini.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoonful into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain fritters of excess oil on paper towel.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: cherry salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together.

title: melt in your mouth rolls
directions: Combine scalded milk, sugar and salt; stir until sugar dissolves.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine yeast and milk mixture.
Add butter and eggs and mix well.
Add flour.
Mix; let rise until double in bulk.
Make out in loaves, rolls, etc.
Let rise and bake.

title: yogurt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 60 to 65 minutes at 325°. Cool in pan for 20 minutes.
A very moist cake.

title: pork chop onion rice bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chops in fat.
Spread rice in bottom of rectangular baking dish.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of onion soup mixture and sprinkle the rest over rice.
Drain mushrooms and save liquid.
Sprinkle mushrooms and pimiento over rice.
Add hot water to mushroom liquid to total 3 cups and pour over rice. Arrange chops on top of rice and sprinkle rest of onion soup over them.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in 350° oven until tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove foil and continue cooking 10 minutes longer or until liquid evaporates.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in the hard butter and mix well.
Add milk and mix quickly.
Turn out on floured surface and knead 10 times.
Put on baking sheet.
Cut with knife just part through. Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add jam and beat well.
Add sifted flour, soda, salt, cloves and allspice, alternating with buttermilk and beating well after each addition until smooth. Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: zucchini or eggplant casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain well.
Add peeled and sliced zucchini or eggplant.
Add tomatoes, cut up.
Simmer until zucchini or eggplant are tender.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix all but caramels together; pour half of the mixture into a greased 13 x 9 pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Melt 50 caramels with the remaining small can of evaporated milk. Spread over hot cake, then evenly pour the chocolate chips on top of caramel. Top with the remaining cake mix and add nuts, if desired; bake another 15 to 18 minutes.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish layer 1/2 of the hamburger, then add a layer of sliced potatoes to cover, another layer of hamburger; top this with another layer of potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with soup and cheese.
Cover with aluminum and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Fry ground beef, chopped onion and pepper in butter until slightly browned. Add canned tomatoes, tomato paste, mushrooms, chopped garlic, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer over low heat for 3 to 4 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Use paper liners in muffin pan.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and lemon peel; mix well.
Stir in blueberries.
In small bowl, combine milk, oil and egg; blend well.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients all at once; stir just until moistened.
Fill muffin liners 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown. Cool 1 minute.
Remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Starting with 1/2 of lettuce, layer ingredients according to recipe, 1/2 of each.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread salad dressing over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle green onions on top and seal bowl and refrigerate.
Toss before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fantastic fish dish
directions: Mix all ingredients except almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with almonds just before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no fuss fudge
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix milk and chocolate bits.
Cook over low heat until smooth.
Add vanilla wafer crumbs and nuts.
Blend together and spread into a buttered 8-inch square pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and bake for 1 hour in an uncovered dish at 350°.

title: baked "3" beans
directions: Drain beans, Add 1/2 of the molasses pork & beans juice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Can be heated in slow cooker.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Stir in milk slowly and cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add seasoning and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add macaroni and transfer to a buttered 1-quart casserole or individual casseroles. Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over macaroni. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 (7 ounce) servings.

title: texas beef bakes
directions: Crumble ground beef into 2-quart dish.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven 45 to 60 minutes.
Stir once.
Top with cheese and return to oven for 3 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, flour, salt, vanilla and syrup.
Stir well.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, garlic powder and onion powder all together.
Place the Chex, Cheerios, pretzels and nuts together in a very large roaster pan.
Pour the butter over the dry mixture; stir carefully and salt to taste. Place in 250° oven and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes.
Be sure to stir because it burns easily.
When taken out of oven, place on absorbent paper and cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chocolate cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oleo margarine until creamy.
Spread by hand in a 13 x 9-inch pan, lightly greased.
Mix together in bowl the cream cheese, 3 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Pour over top of cake mix and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate frosty ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: hearty salad bowl
directions: Marinate and chill green beans, carrots and potatoes in Italian dressing 1 to 2 hours. Mix the vegetables and meat. Arrange the sliced eggs on top of salad. Sprinkle with paprika. This salad can be served hot or cold.

title: tillamook macaroni au gratin
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Meanwhile, combine soup, milk and Tillamook cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese begins to melt.
Mix with macaroni, blending in mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Combine crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle on top of macaroni.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Enjoy.
Super!!

title: dream cake
directions: Bake cake.
After baking, put holes in cake with a wooden spoon.
Heat pineapple and sugar on stove until melted; pour over cake.
Slice bananas; lay on top of pineapple.
Prepare pudding; pour over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle party nuts over top of Cool Whip.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Blend Oreo cookies in blender, including frosting.
Mix with melted margarine to make crust.
Pat half of the crumbs in an 8-inch square pan.
Place the softened ice cream over crumbs.
Pat remaining half of crumbs over ice cream.
Pour hot fudge sauce over the top.
Freeze.
Cut into 4 x 4-inch squares.
Can be stored in the freezer quite a while.

title: baja lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion about 4 minutes (nonstick pan/nonstick spray).
Add tomatoes, chilies, mushrooms, beans, chili powder and cumin.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
In 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch casserole, arrange 1/3 of tortilla strips in single layer.
Set aside some cheese for garnish.
Pour 1/4 of mixture and 1/3 of cheese over strips.

title: fig cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until done, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot cheese biscuits
directions: Cream together cheese and Crisco.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and chill for 1 hour.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Balls will flatten as they cook.

title: oven-roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients; close bag and shake.
Or toss in bowl until vegetables are evenly coated.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice; add pineapple and peaches.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Garnish with fine chopped nuts.
Prepare in advance or set overnight in refrigerator.
This is good for Christmas parties.

title: heloise's angel biscuits
directions: Dough can be kept for up to 3 days in a covered bowl in the fridge. Dissolve yeast in warm water & set aside. Mix the dry ingredients in the order given, cutting in the shortening. Stir in the buttermilk & yeast mixture & blend thoroughly. The dough is ready to refrigerate. When it's time to make the biscuits, turn the dough out on a floured board and knead lightly. Roll out and cut with a biscuit cutter, placing them in a greased pan. Let the dough rise slightly before baking in a 400° oven for 12-15 minutes.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Crush cookies in a zipper-style plastic bag with a rolling pin or in food processor.
Mix cookie crumbs and butter.
Press onto bottom and sides of a 9 inch pie plate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Crush croutons slightly and toss with oleo.
Set aside.
Place broccoli, water and salt in pan.
Bring to boil.
Separate pieces. Remove from heat.
Drain well and set aside.
Place cheese in pan; add cheese and cook over medium heat until cheese is melted. Stir frequently.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart dish.
Sprinkle croutons on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix cherry pie filling with lemon juice and sweetened condensed milk; add bananas, pineapple and nuts, then mix in 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Add the remaining Cool Whip to top of fruit salad.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat the oven to 500°.
Lightly spray or wipe a baking sheet with vegetable oil.
Trim the tops of each eggplant; slice in half lengthwise.
Make 2 deep, lengthwise slashes into the flesh of each half, being careful not to cut through the skin. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Place the halves on the baking sheet, flesh sides down.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until the eggplants are tender and the skin is shriveled.

title: zippy zucchini
directions: Peel and press garlic.
Saute over low heat in olive oil until garlic is light golden, about 10 minutes.
Steam zucchini and mushrooms until tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Place in serving dish.
Pour garlic oil over vegetables.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with cheese and serve.

title: italian broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli in unsalted boiling water 5 to 7 minutes or until broccoli is tender; drain well.

Combine eggs, Cheddar cheese soup and crushed oregano. Stir in stewed tomatoes and cooked broccoli. Turn the vegetable-cheese mixture into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Bake the casserole, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until heated completely through. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: holiday macaroons
directions: Beat eggs in bowl until light; add sugar gradually, beating for 5 minutes or until thickened.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in butter, vanilla, lemon rind and coconut. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased and floured cookie sheet. Decorate with candied cherries.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Cool completely.
Store in tightly covered container.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: meatballs
directions: In
bowl,
mix	1/4 cup soup, beef, crumbs, egg, celery and 1/4
teaspoon ginger.
Shape into 50 meatballs.
Place in jelly roll pan.
Broil 4-inches from heat about 10 minutes or until done, turning once. Drain.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and evaporated milk in kettle and bring to a boil.
Boil 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining items.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan and cool.

title: goulash-felstow style
directions: Brown meat in frying pan or Dutch oven.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve in soup bowls with hot biscuits or rolls.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding mix with corn syrup. Gradually add milk and eggs, stirring to blend, then add pecans. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° until top is firm and begins to crack. Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup, water and Lipton onion soup together. Spread rice on bottom of shallow pan or casserole.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture over rice.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice mixture.
Pour rest of soup mix over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.
Remove foil and let chicken brown slightly.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° and 25 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Use an 8-inch square of heavy-duty foil.
Place chicken in center.
Mound rice on chicken.
Pour on liquid.
Season.
Dot with oleo.
Cook over coals for about 1 hour.

title: cole slaw and dressing
directions: In one large mixing bowl, combine mustard, sugar, pineapple juice, white vinegar, white pepper and salt.
Wisk together, then wisk in mayonnaise.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil your chicken; drain.
Add your noodles, cheese and your two soups.
Chop your bell peppers and onion.
Add to your chicken, then add your Ro-Tel and stir; serve.

title: nanaimo cookies
directions: Put 1/2 cup butter, sugar, unsweetened chocolate, and vanilla in top of double boiler until blended.
Add egg and cook 5 minutes, stirring.
Add crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Press firmly into buttered 9x9x2- inch pan.
Cool and chill 15 minutes.
Cream 1/2 cup butter, beat in pudding mix and milk.
Add confectionary sugar gradually and beat until smooth.
Spread over first layer. Chill 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate in 1 tablespoon butter over low heat. Spread over layer and chill till firm.
Cut into 1 inch squares.
Keep in refrigerator.
May be frozen.
Makes 81 pieces.

title: chicken cordon blue(serves 6)
directions: Mix gravy mix with white wine.
Add cold water.
Add mushrooms.
Stir to mix.
Heat in saucepan, then place chicken in casserole dish.
Cover with mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Thicken gravy with 2 tablespoons flour and cold water, if necessary.
Pour over chicken.
Serve with rice.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add flour, vanilla and potato chips; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes, or until browned on edges. Yields approximately 70 or 80 cookies.

title: ham and egg casserole
directions: Spread butter on both sides of bread; cut into cubes.
Combine bread cubes, meat, cheese and seasoning.
Stir well.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in milk and egg mixture to meat mixture.
Stir well.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn flakes and 1/4 cup butter. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine corn flakes with 1/4 cup butter and top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar, pour in pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Put frozen strawberries in liquid to thaw.
Prepare 45 minutes before serving.

title: pesto lasagne
directions: Filling:
Clean and stem spinach.
Chop very fine.
Set aside. In a large, heavy skillet, saute onion in 2 tablespoons of olive oil (rest of oil is for noodles) until soft, 5 to 8 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Stir spinach into hot onions. Transfer into large bowl.
Add half of grated Parmesan cheese, the pesto, Ricotta and sunflower seeds.
Grind in some extra pepper. Mix thoroughly.
Set aside.

title: low-fat chicken broccoli divan
directions: In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange broccoli and chicken. In small bowl, combine soup, water and pepper; pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, or until hot and bubbling.
Garnish with sliced plum tomatoes, if desired.

title: peanut butterscotch krispie cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch bits in double boiler.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter; blend well.
Pour over cereal; stir.
Put into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Let cool in refrigerator.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie crust lightly.
Cream sugar and butter; add the cocoa, vanilla and eggs.
Beat for 10 minutes. Pour in pie shell and chill overnight.

title: applesaucy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: swedish oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine oats, flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Blend in buttermilk, eggs, melted butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Let batter stand for 30 to 45 minutes. (Batter will thicken; do not blend in additional liquid.)

title: pot roast and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place roast in a baking dish; put roast in oven and cook for 90 minutes.
Add vegetables and more water, if needed, and cook another 60 minutes.
Check to see if roast is tender with a fork.
Bake another 30 minutes, if needed.
Roast should be mildly brown, not overdone, or rare and evenly cooked through.

title: date-apple bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and milk.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir well.
Add apples, dates and nuts.
Put in 2 prepared loaf pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: buttermilk donuts
directions: Add sugar to eggs.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in potatoes, shortening and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients and mix only until flour is completely moistened.
Chill dough 1 hour or overnight.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Mix jello with hot water until dissolved, then add cold water and put in refrigerator until partially set.
Add all other ingredients and let it "set up" in refrigerator.
De-mold on lettuce.
Pretty and delicious.

title: christmas wassail bowl
directions: In a very large pan (Dutch oven) bring cider and sugar just to a boil to dissolve the sugar.
Remove from heat.

title: southern casserole
directions: Mix all together; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve
jello
in
hot water.
Save 1/4 mixture to be used later.
Into the rest of the jello, mix together bananas, strawberries
and
pineapple.
Put	in refrigerator until congealed.	To
the
softened cream cheese add the cup of confectioners
sugar
and the vanilla (set aside).	In another bowl, beat the whipping cream.
Add this to the cream cheese mixture along
with 1/4 cup of reserved jello.
Put this on top of the congealed salad and sprinkle with chopped nuts if desired.
Be sure not to leave out more than 1/4 cup of the gelatin and hot water
mixture
or the bottom layer will not jell.	This is so good it could be served for salad or dessert.

title: venison swiss steak
directions: Brown battered steaks in oil.
Remove and saute onion and celery.
Replace venison.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until venison is tender.
Hint:
Serve sauce over noodles or rice.

title: country spinach
directions: Put spinach in saucepan.
Add water; cook until tender. Drain; add butter.
Stir and add egg.
Stir.
Put back on stove with lid over very low heat until all the egg is done.
You will need to stir the mixture.
Drain off all the liquid.
Salt to taste.

title: red ketchup
directions: Stir all ingredients, except sugar and clear-jel, together in large kettle.
Boil down for 1 1/2 to 3 hours, then add the sugar. Mix the clear-jel with cold water; add to thicken.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Mix the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together in a microwave-safe bowl.
Heat for 60 to 90 seconds in microwave. When they are soft, mix together well.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper on a cookie sheet.
Refrigerate for several hours until firm.
Makes about 60 to 70 clusters.

title: garbage
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter together.
Fold in cereal, raisins, peanuts and coat.
Pour box of powdered sugar over mixture and with fork in each hand. Stir gently to coat with sugar.
(I use a large bowl, just dump everything into a bowl and it's much easier to coat with powdered sugar.
Cool and store in airtight container.)

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until blended.
Stuff between the leaves of artichokes.
Stand in saucepan and pour in about 1 inch of water.
Place about 1 teaspoon olive oil over each artichoke. On low to medium flame, let steam until you can pull out one of the outside leaves easily.
Makes 3 stuffed artichokes.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and Karo in a 3 quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies. Press mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together over hot, not boiling, water, stirring until well blended.
Remove from heat and spread over Rice Krispie mixture.
Cool until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix altogether and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Chill and serve with whipped topping.

title: goldilocks' gourmet spinach soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan, then saute mushrooms and scallions until tender.
Add flour and stir just until flour is cooked.
Whisk in chicken broth and then milk, stirring until thickened.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg, cream cheese and Swiss cheese; stir until melted.
Then stir in spinach.
Heat and stir very gently.
Season to taste.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine together sweet potatoes, salt and 1/2-cup boiling water in saucepan.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until tender.
Pour off all but 1/4 cup stock.
Dot with butter and set aside.

title: easy oven fried fish
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Separate fillets and pat dry with paper towel.
Combine beaten egg white, grapefruit or orange juice concentrate and Worcestershire sauce.
In another bowl, combine crushed crackers and wheat germ.
Dip fish fillets into egg white mixture, then in the crumb mixture.
Arrange fillets in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, tucking under any thin edges so fish will be uniform in thickness and cook evenly.
Drizzle the melted butter or margarine evenly over fish.
Bake in a 500° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks that have been well beaten.
Sift the flour, salt and baking powder together, then add alternately with milk.
Add the vanilla and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: swedish cucumber salad
directions: Stir together vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper until sugar is dissolved. Stir in dill; set aside. Rinse cucumbers well; peel, leaving a few long narrow strips of peel on cucumbers. Slice paper-thin and add to marinade. Toss gently. Cover and chill well. Serve with chicken, meat, fish or sandwiches. Makes 4 side-dish servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick butter and graham cracker crumbs together and press in bowl or dish for crust.

title: monkey bread *
directions: Dissolve yeast in water for 4 minutes; add sugar, salt and eggs.
Beat thoroughly; add milk alternately with flour.
Add 1/4 pound melted butter.
Cover and let double in size.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick, cut in strips 2 inches long by 1 inch wide.
Dip each strip in melted butter and place in tube pan 5 layers deep.
Let rise and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.
Will slice or pull apart.
When reheating, wrap in foil and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon water.
Makes two pans.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Put sugar, margarine and milk into large saucepan.
Cook until mixture forms hard ball in water.
Grease pan with butter to pour candy into.
When it has formed ball, add Marshmallow Creme and chocolate pieces until dissolved.
Then add vanilla and nuts. Pour quickly into greased dish or pan and cool, then serve.

title: dippers nuggets chicken
directions: In deep fryer, place oil, filling to no more than 1/2 full. Heat to medium temperature.

title: ham chowder
directions: Dice vegetables.
In soup kettle, cook vegetables in water or ham broth until tender, about 20 minutes.
Add ham, butter, salt and pepper.
Blend flour into milk.
Stir into soup.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Turn heat to low and allow to simmer, partially covered, 10 to 20 minutes.
Garnish with paprika and chopped parsley.

title: cherry angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir flour and 3/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar together.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy; add remaining sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time. Beat until stiff peaks form; fold in flavorings.
Sprinkle flour mixture and cherries over top.
Fold in gently just until flour mixture disappears.
Push batter into ungreased tube pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain green beans and corn.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Spread evenly in greased casserole dish.
Mix onions, celery, cheese, sour cream and soup.
Spread over beans and corn.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed crackers and almonds.
Spread this over top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate layer bars
directions: Combine chocolate chips, cream cheese and evaporated milk in saucepan.
Melt and mix on very low heat; add walnuts and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Press 1/2 mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chocolate mixture on top.
Sprinkle rest of mixture on top of filling.
Bake
at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.
When cold, cut into bars or squares.

title: mocha sparkle
directions: Combine cornstarch and water in top of double boiler.
Add sugar, cinnamon, chocolate and coffee.
Cook over boiling water until thick.
Add milk.
Heat 15 minutes while stirring often. Chill.
Top with whipped cream and serve cold.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: jerky - antelope or deer
directions: Open fresh loaf of bread.
Put one slice of bread in left hand.
Put another slice of bread in right hand.
Move left hand towards the right hand and the right hand towards the left.
Whaw!! the slices of bread are jammed together--Thus--a Jam Sandwich.

title: coconut candy
directions: Put coconut in cloth and squeeze all juice out.
Boil sugar in coconut milk 5 minutes.
Add coconut and boil 10 minutes or longer.
Set in a pan of cool water and beat until creamy.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix together Bisquick and cold water to form dough.
Divide dough into two balls and roll each into rectangle shape.
Divide sausage in half and spread/pat onto rolled dough.
Roll dough and sausage jelly-roll style.
Freeze slightly to make slicing easier. Slice rolls into 1/8-inch slices and arrange on ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Can easily be frozen.

title: crock-pot hamburger stew
directions: Brown and rinse hamburger.
Combine all the ingredients in a large crock-pot.
Cook on high all day.
May put in large kettle in the oven and cook at 275° for 6 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Cut up tops of broccoli.
Add bacon and cheese.
Mix together mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar. Stir in broccoli.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or longer to marinate and serve.

title: barbecue
directions: Ground beef and onions are to be browned thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.
If too bitter, add 1 or 2 tablespoons of sugar.

title: zucchini cups
directions: Cook until zucchini is transparent and sugar is melted and syrupy.
Dissolve 2 tablespoons cornstarch in small amount of water; add to zucchini mixture to thicken.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: aloha cheese ball
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and blend well.
Spoon into 1-quart mold.
Chill.
Combine the next 5 ingredients and blend well.
Spread over first layer.
Refrigerate overnight; unmold. Garnish top layer with coconut and pecan halves, if desired.

title: calico bean hot dish
directions: Saute hamburger, bacon and onion until lightly browned.
Drain only a small amount of liquid from beans.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 300°. For faster cooking, bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: don strange's double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/4 cup oil.
Add boiling water and stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining oil.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Blend completely.

title: nestle fudge
directions: Combine margarine, milk, sugar and salt in medium size heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil-lined square baking pan. Chill until firm.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Cook in large vessel, stirring constantly.
Cook to a soft ball.
Take off and add vanilla.
Whip until creamy and add pecans at once.
Pour into buttered pan and, when cool, cut into pieces.

title: garden patch corn
directions: In 2-quart saucepan melt butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except tomato and parsley.
Cover and cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in tomato and parsley.
Cover and let stand 1 minute.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: If you use plain flour, add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon soda to the ingredients.

title: vienna-n-noodles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook onion, celery and carrots in margarine or butter for 5 minutes.
Stir in the flour, salt and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, noodles and vienna sausages. Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: stewed onions
directions: Wash onions, cut onions in about 4-inch long pieces.
Put in water to cover.
Add chicken bouillon cubes and vegetable oil. Cook until almost done.
Mix 1 cup of cornmeal to a stiff consistency with hot water.
Shape dough into small flat cakes. Drop in skillet with onions.
Cook about 10 more minutes.
Serves about 5 people.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Add butter and stir.
Then add peanut butter until melted.
Pour contents over the raw oatmeal.
Stir quickly and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Makes fudgie cookies.

title: chicken pockets with spinach and cheese(serves  6; diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saut onion in oil until limp. Add carrot and cook 2 to 3 minutes. Add garlic, thyme and spinach. Cover and cook until spinach wilts. Pour off excess water. Salt and pepper to taste. Allow to cool. Divide into 6 portions. Cut pocket in side of each chicken half. Stuff each with spinach filling. Close with toothpicks.

title: nonfat banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Add sour cream to pudding mixture, then add Cool Whip.
Layer pan with wafers, then put bananas.
Add pudding and keep alternating the layers.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, pour oil.
Add onions and cook 5 minutes. Stir in ground beef and garlic; brown.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Simmer on very low heat, stirring often, for 3 or 4 hours.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine all; mix well and bake in a moderate oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add flour, salt and soda.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Mix.
Form dough in rolls, 1 to 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill; slice cookies about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pistou
directions: In a mortar, pound the garlic to a paste with the basil and parsley; add the tomato paste and cheese.
Beat in the oil by droplets, then beat in 1 cup of hot soup.
Pour the sauce into a small bowl and pass it around with Garden Soup.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli just until tender.
Put in bottom of casserole. Melt 1/2 stick of butter in medium pan.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk and bouillon cubes and cook until thick.
Pour over broccoli.
Prepare Stove Top as per box directions using other half of butter.
Pat on top of broccoli.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: In large saucepan, saute onions and garlic in oil.
Add parsley, tomatoes, tomato paste and water.
Stir well.
Add salt, pepper, basil and bay leaf.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: cooked icing
directions: Place ingredients in a pan; cook until mixture separates from sides of pan, approximately 2 to 5 minutes.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Cool about 5 minutes and pour over cake.
Do not spread.

title: pumpkin nut cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in the order listed.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: mary pearl's fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together the eggs, oil, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add sugar; beat.
Slowly blend in flour with soda and salt.
Blend well.
Add pecans; stir.
Fold in chopped apples last.
Bake in heavy Bundt or tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: In large bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Dip chicken in margarine, then in crumb mixture.
Place in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear.
Serves 6.

title: one bowl cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in flour alternately with milk, vanilla and lemon juice.
Don't beat too long.
Bake for 70 to 90 minutes in a tube or loaf pan.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs until light. Add sugar, sweet potatoes, salt, melted butter, milk, lemon juice and nutmeg. Pour into unbaked 9-inch shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until custard is set. Pumpkin may be substituted for sweet potatoes. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake mix according to package.
Pour half of the batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together egg, buttermilk, green onions and water.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
In a heavy saucepan or deep fat fryer, heat about 2 inches oil to 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoons into hot oil.
Fry a few at a time, about 2 minutes, or until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in 325° oven while frying remainder.
Makes about 18.

title: cheese cake(no bake)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and place firmly on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.

title: fried rice(wok recipe)
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of peanut oil in a preheated wok.
Turn heat down to medium.
Beat eggs and pepper with a fork in a small bowl. Pour 1/3 of egg mixture into wok.
Swirl wok gently so egg covers bottom of wok.
Cook over medium heat until egg mixture sets, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove egg from wok and cut into thin strips.

title: ham with pineapple sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place ham on rack in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 2 1/4 hours until done.
Meanwhile for sauce, in medium saucepan cook onion in margarine until tender, not brown.
Stir catsup, preserves and dry mustard.
Heat through. Brush sauce onto ham before serving; pass remaining.
Serves 16 to 24.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Rinse under running cold water and drain.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix broth, half and half, flour, butter, salt and pepper in a 3-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute.
Stir in spaghetti, turkey, olives and almonds. Spread in ungreased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until hot and bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs and beat thoroughly. Sift flour and spices together; add to shortening mixture.	Blend thoroughly.
Lightly stir in raisins, oats, coconut and pecans. This will be hard to mix and you may have to mix with your hands. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until very lightly browned.

title: calcutta chicken spread
directions: Mix ingredients and serve with sesame crackers.

title: imperial crab
directions: In a bowl with crabmeat, add green pepper, some parsley and bread.
In a small bowl, beat together the egg, salad dressing or mayonnaise, dry mustard, salt, pepper and butter.

title: snack tree
directions: Put on tree.
Fun for overnight friends.

title: taco dip
directions: Smooth cream cheese evenly on the bottom of a glass baking dish, round or 9 x 9-inch.
Spread chili over cream cheese. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on chili.
Place in microwave just until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: apple bread-and-butter pudding
directions: Peel the apples and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
In a large frying pan, melt 4 tablespoons of butter over medium-high heat. Add the apples and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Heat the oven to 325°.
Use the remaining butter to butter one side of each slice of bread. Line the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart baking dish with half of the bread, buttered side up.
Cut the remaining bread into 8 triangles.
Beat the eggs and 1/2 cup of the remaining sugar until light.
Beat in the milk, 1/4 teaspoon of cinnamon and the vanilla.
Put the apples on top of bread in the pan and arrange the triangles around the edge.
Pour the milk mixture over all and let stand 10 minutes.
Combine the remaining 1 tablespoon of sugar with 1/8 teaspoon of cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Bake until golden brown around the edges and the custard is set, about 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked chicken wings
directions: Wash chicken wings and pat dry.
In skillet, saute chicken wings in melted butter until lightly browned.
Arrange in oiled baking dish; add tomatoes and celery.
In a separate bowl, mix soy sauce, vinegar and salt.
Pour over the chicken.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Place jar of peanut butter in water to soften.
Melt chocolate, peanut butter and butter.
Drop 1 tablespoon mixture in each cup.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Smooth top.
(May use a bit of paraffin melted with mixture if desired.)

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix water, vinegar and egg; add to flour and salt mixed with shortening.
Roll out amount needed.
Rest can be frozen until later.
Makes three 8 or 9-inch crusts.

title: cinnamon blintzes
directions: Trim bread and roll out until thin.
Cream the cream cheese, egg yolks and sugar.
Spread thinly on the bread.
Roll up.
Melt butter.
In separate bowl mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dip rolls first in butter then in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place close together on cookie sheet.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer and slice each roll in half.
Put in oven straight from freezer on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: poached salmon steaks with zucchini noodles
directions: Place salmon in a large nonstick skillet that has been coated with cooking spray.
Combine milk and bouillon granules; pour over fish.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Cook and stir bell peppers, onion and garlic in 1/4 cup Miracle Whip over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken, juice, cumin, ground red pepper and remaining 1/4 cup Miracle Whip.
Cook about 10 minutes, or until chicken is cooked through. Serve on tortillas.

title: broccoli and olive salad
directions: Combine broccoli, olives, onion, eggs and nuts.
Serve chilled in a bowl or over honeydew melon slices.

title: muerbe teig(pie crust from germany)
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Add egg yolk and mix.
Pat mixture into ungreased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: plantation cake
directions: Bake gingerbread as directed on package.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Heat lemon pudding until hot through.
Top warm gingerbread squares with cream cheese.
Spoon hot lemon pudding over top.
Serves 9.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat; break into bite size pieces.
Remove from skillet and drain.
Brown onion and bell pepper in meat drippings; drain onion and pepper.
Stir together the beans, brown sugar, molasses, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and black pepper.
Mix in meat, onion and bell pepper.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: every sunday homemade ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in ice cream freezer; stir well.
Start freezer and let run until it begins to slow down or ice cream begins to thicken.
(May add fruit to make any flavor.)

title: phyllis' broccoli spaghetti
directions: Bring 1 quart of water with salt to a boil.
Add spaghetti. Immediately after that, add broccoli cut into bite size pieces. When spaghetti is done, drain spaghetti-broccoli in colander.
Put into a large bowl.
Melt butter with garlic cloves in microwave; pour over spaghetti-broccoli mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over spaghetti-broccoli.
Toss slightly and serve immediately.

title: oven chow mein
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add enough water to make 2 1/4 cups liquid.
Mix rice and beef mixture and liquid together in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp or crab dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with remainder of ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving with chips or crackers.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs, remove from pan while you melt butter and add rest of ingredients in frying pan.
Add while hot to ribs.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, test if not well done.
Roast awhile longer.
Or you can use slow cooker method.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk over hot water in top of double boiler or over very low heat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, sugar, water and egg; beat until blended.
Add half of the flour, butter and salt; stir until blended.
Add remaining flour, stirring until blended.

title: gourmet asparagus crepes
directions: Place the ham, cheese and asparagus in the crepe center and roll, placing seam face down, on greased casserole dish, 9 x 12-inch.

title: roasted glazed chicken breast
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in roasting pan.
Combine apple juice, cornstarch and cinnamon in a small saucepan, mixing well to blend cornstarch.
Add lemon slices.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove lemon slices and spoon part of the glaze over the chicken breasts.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Pat down in oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or less.
DO NOT OVERBAKE.
Over low heat, melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over baked mixture.
Cut in bars when cooled.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat and onions until done.
Drain, add soups, sauce and milk.
Remove from heat.
Take 3 to 4 tortillas and tear in bite size pieces in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Add some of the meat/soup mixture; then some cheese.
Layer, being sure to end with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, green pepper and tomato sauce.
Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions; stir in 1/2 can onions.
Spoon corn muffin batter around edge of beef mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes or until corn bread is done.
Top corn bread with cheese and remaining onions; bake, uncovered, for 1 to 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Blend cheese and sour cream.
Add soup mix and Worcestershire. Cut crust off bread and flatten with rolling pin.
Spread with mixture and roll up.
Cut into thirds.
Cut bacon and wrap around rolls; secure with toothpicks.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 15 minutes.
Yield:

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and cool. Combine vegetables with enough salad dressing to coat.
Pour over pasta and toss.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: apple salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine apple and sugar.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and stir until combined.
Cool.
Fold in apples, nuts, celery and whipped topping.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Cake:
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, eggs, vanilla and pecans in large bowl.
Melt 1 stick butter with 3 tablespoons cocoa.
Pour in with ingredients and mix well.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When finished and cool, put (half) marshmallows on top of cake.

title: honey barbecue spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving size pieces.
Place ribs, bone side down on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Cover and roast at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain.
Combine all the remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Brush some of glaze on ribs.
Roast, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes longer until meat is tender.
Brush occasionally with remaining glaze.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cookie cutouts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Take a large bowl and soften butter; mix in your sugar to a paste (use wooden spoon).
Mix egg and vanilla; blend all dry ingredients together and mix into your batter until it is thick.
Chill your dough.
Take only 1/2 of the batter and roll out onto the floured table.
Cut out your shapes using the cutters.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion in skillet; drain off grease. Add green beans well drained.
Add tomato soup and seasoning.
Put in pie shell and add top crust.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: jello cake(portuguese)
directions: Make the Jell-O but only let it set (jell) about 1 hour.
It should not be watery. Take Jell-O and mix in 1 container of Cool Whip.
Cut up the cake into bite size pieces.
Cut up the strawberries.
Place this mixture into an angel cake tube pan and put in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
After the cake has cooled, tip over in a plate and
frost with the second container of Cool Whip.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, mix flour and sugar and cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: apple nut bread
directions: At low speed blend oil, eggs (add eggs, one at a time), apples and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes in ungreased loaf pan.
Cool 20 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut up the vegetables and pour dressing over top.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and the cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice and blueberries.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Keep blueberry mixture warm in oven.
Cut shortening into flour, 1 tablespoon sugar, baking powder and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in milk.
Drop dough by 6 spoonfuls onto hot blueberry mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until topping is golden brown.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening well.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavoring and beat again.
Add dry ingredients alternately with cream; start with flour and end with flour.
Add walnuts which have been lightly floured.
Bake in greased and floured tube cake pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool cake 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Drain sweet potatoes, reserving some liquid.
Mash the potatoes, adding enough liquid for a smooth consistency.
Add maple syrup.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: cider beef stew dinner
directions: In bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper; add beef and toss to coat.
In large pan, brown beef in oil.
Add cider, water, vinegar and thyme; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add carrots, celery, potato and onion; return to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put ground beef in water and add salt in a large kettle with tight-fitting lid.
Cook on low heat until beef is done.
Add the vegetables and pepper.
Cook on high until mixture begins to boil, then reduce heat to low setting.
Cook for 1 hour or until vegetables are done.
Any leftover soup may be frozen.

title: pineapple-sweet potato casserole
directions: Slice yams into 1/2-inch pieces or mash. Combine with pineapple, butter, sugar and cinnamon in 2-quart casserole. Microwave 4 minutes on High. Stir. Sprinkle top with pecans and brown sugar. Microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes more.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat the cream cheese and Italian seasoning together with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, pizza sauce, then the other 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and the green and red pepper.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with breadsticks.
Makes 10 servings.

title: stuffing balls
directions: Cook celery, onion and parsley in butter.
Add bouillon cubes. Pour over bread.
Add egg and 1/4 cup milk.
Shape in balls the size of golf balls and place them in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix soups with the remaining milk.
Cover bottom of pan with soup mixture.
Spoon remaining soup over top of stuffing balls.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: party punch - ethiopia
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large punch bowl.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: camper's pullet(recipe based on 2 pound boneless breasts)
directions: Sprinkle chicken (both sides) with Good Seasons.
Saute in olive oil and butter until golden.
Remove chicken; add flour. Cook 2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Add chicken and cook for 40 minutes.
Can be done on top of stove or in oven.
Add parsley before serving over rice.
Easily doubles.

title: esther's icebox fruit cake
directions: Place margarine, marshmallows, orange juice and condensed milk in saucepan or microwave and heat until marshmallows are melted. Remove from heat and add crumbs, then other ingredients.
Mix well and press into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Refrigerate.
May wrap and freeze.
Keeps well up to a year in freezer.

title: frozen banana punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water in bowl; cool.
Add pineapple juice and orange juice.
Mash bananas in bowl.
Add lemon juice. Combine with juices; mix well.
Pour into freezer container. Freeze until firm.
Remove 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Mash until slushy.
Combine with ginger ale in large punch bowl; mix gently.
Makes 50 servings.

title: grandmother's famous cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda into a large bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Add orange peel, orange juice and egg.
Stir until moist.
Fold in cranberries and raisins.

title: sally's corn pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, water and salt and bring to a rolling boil.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Cut shortening into flour as for pie dough.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into a small ball, then roll in sesame seed. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: the best bean casserole
directions: Drain first three beans and save 1/2 the liquid.
Fry bacon and onion, then add the bean liquid and mustard, vinegar, sugar and garlic powder.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Mix with beans.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chicken pie with sweet potato crust
directions: Put layer of chicken in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add a layer of green pepper and a layer of onions.
Sprinkle generously with parsley.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Melt butter over moderate heat; blend in flour and add chicken broth slowly, stirring until sauce thickens and is smooth.
Add lemon peel, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Top with Sweet Potato Crust and bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: broccoli dip
