directions: Combine drained, cooked broccoli and remaining ingredients. Heat and serve from chafing dish with tortilla chips.
Flavor improves if made the day before.

title: spice nuts
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Cook to soft ball stage; remove from heat and add walnuts.
Stir until well covered.
Turn onto foil and separate.
When dry, store in fruit jar.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat until cheeses are melted.
Keep warm in crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips, breadsticks or even on spaghetti.
Makes 4 to 5 cups.

title: angel cake with chocolate
directions: Melt chocolate.
Beat yolks with water and sugar.
Add chocolate and cook until a custard consistency, then cool.
Add vanilla and beaten egg whites.
Break up an angel food cake in large bite size pieces.
Place a layer on bottom of large cake pan, then a layer of chocolate mixture, then another layer of cake and chocolate.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with coconut. Store in refrigerator.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: chocolate coconut crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, butter, eggs and sugar.
Add coconut, nuts, cornflakes, oats and chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: turtle bars
directions: Combine caramels and 1/4 cup milk in heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until caramels are melted.
Set aside. Combine butter, dry cake mix, nuts and 1/4 cup milk and mix until crumbly.
Press half of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread caramel mixture over chocolate chips. Return pan to oven and bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.
Do not bake longer than 18 minutes or bars will be hard and dry.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter; add eggs and pecans.
Fill pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage strata
directions: Combine beaten eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Place a layer of bread in flat casserole dish.
Spread cooked sausage over bread. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Add a layer of bread.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Add a little grated cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in your hot water.
Mix in cream cheese (cut in small pieces).
Add cola and juice.
When mixture begins to thicken, add pineapple and nuts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a very large bowl, blend sugar, eggs and oil thoroughly. Slowly add the remaining ingredients, mixing very well.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
A large coffee can also can be used, if you would like to mail this bread as a gift.
Pour the mixture into the tube pan or coffee can and bake at 350° for about an hour. Test if done with a toothpick in the middle.
Toothpick should come out clean but do not overcook.
Bread is very moist and delicious!

title: zucchini loaf
directions: Mix eggs, oil and Bisquick.
Add remaining ingredients, leaving zucchini for last.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown meats and onion together. Drain.
Add chili, taco sauce and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Mix all together.
Add cheese.
Stir frequently until cheese is melted.
Serve over tortilla chips. Top with sour cream, lettuce, shredded cheese, tomatoes or other favorite toppings.

title: rum cookies
directions: Put molasses in a cup and fill to 1/2 cup full with rum.
Mix with crushed vanilla waters, 1 cup powdered sugar and toasted and chopped walnuts.
Roll in balls and roll balls in powdered sugar. Makes 3 dozen.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg in medium mixing bowl.
Add Eagle Brand milk and mix together.
Add lemon juice and mix together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Garnish with twisted lemon slice.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Serve cold.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon and debone.
Clear away all dark skin.
Add crushed crackers and rest of ingredients.
Mix well and pat into small patties and fry in small amount of grease until browned.

title: orange frosted
directions: Mix orange juice, sherbet and vanilla ice cream in a large punch bowl.
Stir in chilled ginger ale. Serve.

title: pop up rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Melt a pat of butter in each muffin tin or grease with oil.
Pour mixture into muffin tins and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Yields 9 rolls.

title: molded asparagus salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, 1 cup water and salt. Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes. Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup water. Add to vinegar mixture, stirring until dissolved. Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in remaining ingredients except mayonnaise.
Spoon mixture into a large Pyrex casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) or 1 1/2-quart mold and chill until firm. Serve with mayonnaise.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Combine boiling water, jello, pineapple and bananas.
Place 1/2 of mixture in a glass dish.
Stir in 1 package of strawberries (still frozen) until they break up.
Cool mixture in refrigerator until firm.
Once mixture is firm, spread sour cream on top.
Take remaining mixture; add second package of strawberries to it and mix.
Place on top of sour cream layer.
Allow to chill and set for at least 1 hour.

title: green tomato bread
directions: Combine first ingredients; set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar, oil, lemon juice and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in tomatoes.
Add ingredients; stir just into mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk. Knead lightly on floured surface.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter. Place on baking sheet; brush top with melted butter.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add milk, then flour and salt. Continue beating until batter is smooth.
Divide 2 tablespoons of roast beef drippings into twelve 3-inch muffin cups.
Tilt to coat evenly.
Heat muffin pan in a 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Pour 2 1/2 tablespoons batter in each greased cup.
Bake at same heat for 30 minutes.
Loosen pudding; transfer to platter.
Serve immediately with roast beef.

title: great grandma's banana cake from 1880
directions: Blend butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add bananas, salt and vanilla.
Dissolve baking soda in sour milk.
Add alternately with flour.
Bake in loaf or layer pan at 350° for 1/2 hour or until done.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In large pan or bowl, mix hot water, oleo or shortening, sugar and salt.
When shortening is melted, add condensed milk.
When lukewarm, add yeast mixture and eggs.
Stir and knead in about 28 cups flour or until a little tacky.
Let rise until double in bulk and knead down when the dough rises the second time.
Put in pans and let rise until double in size.
Bake in 350° oven.
Makes 10 dozen.
You can 1/2 this recipe for 5 dozen.

title: lamb with aioli - mustard marinade
directions: Blend yolk in with garlic and pinch of salt.
Whisk in oil, drop by drop, until thickens.
Whisk in remainder in a steady stream.
Thin with a little lemon juice to taste.
Add mustard, thyme, rosemary, soy sauce and ginger.
Add salt to taste. Marinate lamb for several hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, salt and milk together in saucepan (an iron skillet is better).
Cook to soft ball stage, when dropped into cold water, the syrup forms a soft ball when rolled between fingers or 236°.
Remove from heat until thickened.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8 x 3-inch baking dish.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove the stems from the mushrooms.
Set the mushroom caps aside.
Chop the stems.

title: arizona salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with dry Jell-O.
Chill for 3 hours before serving.

title: mabel's meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Sprinkle on salt and cream of tarter.
Beat in.
Add sugar gradually and beat to make stiff peaks.
Fold in corn flakes, chocolate bits and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° about 15-18 minutes or until firm to touch.

title: barbecue pork roast
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over pork roast.
Bake at 350° (30 minutes for each pound) or can be cooked in slow cooker. Take meat off bone; chop into small pieces and add to drippings.

title: orange chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 10-inch skillet.
In mixing bowl, combine orange juice, tamari, molasses, mustard, garlic powder, green pepper, cinnamon and ginger.
Pour over chicken.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover.
Simmer for 45 to 50 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Keep warm on serving platter. Combine arrowroot and water.
Add to remaining pan juices.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes until mixture thickens.
Pour over chicken. Garnish with orange slices.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over fresh fruit.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
Toss and serve.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.
Is excellent accompaniment for roast beef or lamb.

title: creamy vegetables
directions: In a saucepan, mix the soup, milk and vegetables.
Heat to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat, cover and continue to cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Stir in cheese until melted.

title: spring punch
directions: *Food Lion brand works great.

title: heavenly potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skin on.
While potatoes are cooking, blend soup and butter until melted.
Add cheese and sour cream.
Blend. Peel and cut up potatoes; add soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in greased casserole dish.

title: meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk. Then mix thoroughly with hamburger, salt & pepper. Shape into balls. Place in casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over meatballs. Bake at 375° until done.

title: dump cake
directions: "Dump" ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan in the order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package, except use 1/2 less water.
Add 1 can cherry pie filling to mix.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions. Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions in diagonal rows across top.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: fudgie scotch squares
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spray a 9 x 9-inch pan and press mixture in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Then add package of Doritos taco chips, broken into pieces, on top.
Serve.

title: old fashioned fudgegroves, texas
directions: Thoroughly combine dry mix in a heavy saucepan.
Stir in milk and bring to a boil.
Stir constantly or until soft ball shapes in a cup of tap water.

title: crab and shrimp salad
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; drain macaroni. Cut up the crab meat. In a small bowl, add all ingredients and seasoning. Mix well and refrigerate until chilled and serve.

title: bean and potato casserole
directions: Drain beans and potatoes.
Melt butter, add to the soup and milk.
Pour over beans and potatoes in a casserole.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cabbage peanut slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: milky way cake
directions: In double boiler, melt Milky Way bars and 1 stick butter until smooth.
In bowl, beat 1 stick butter, sugar and eggs (one at a time).
Sift flour and soda and alternately add with milk and vanilla.
Add candy and pecans.
Bake for 1 hour in 300° oven in a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased and floured).

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on plate. Top with ground beef mixed with nacho seasoning. Top with salsa, black olives, green peppers and taco cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips. Enjoy!

title: great picnic baked beans
directions: Combine beans, molasses and brown sugar in casserole.
Slice bacon in 1/4-inch pieces.
Top casserole with bacon strips.
Bake uncovered 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: tomato salad
directions: Dice tomatoes.
Chop onions, parsley and mint leaves.

title: crispy chicken strips
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/2-inch thickness, then cut into 1-inch strips. In a bowl, combine potato flakes and bread crumbs. In another bowl, lightly beat eggs. Add a dash of salt and black pepper. Dip chicken in the egg mixture, then in the potato mixture. In a skillet, cook chicken strips in medium-hot oil for 4 to 5 minutes, until golden brown.

title: mission cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Simmer onions
in
melted
butter
Add	seafood and hot milk. In a
small bowl combine wine and flour;
add cream and mix well. Stir
into	seafood
mixture
and
bring to a boil. Simmer 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley for serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: reese's p-nut butter pie
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions.
Add peanut butter to hot pudding. Pour into pie shell and refrigerate.

title: deep dish chicken pie
directions: Melt margarine over low heat; add flour and stir until smooth. Cook for 1 minute.
Gradually add broth and cook over medium heat, stirring, until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Stir in salt, pepper, peas, eggs and chicken.
Spoon into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cut pastry into strips and arrange on top of chicken mixture.
Lightly brush pastry with egg mixture.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix well and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and dice.
Place in baking dish.
Fry bacon until crisp, drain well, crumble and add to potatoes.
Add mayonnaise.
Grate Velveeta cheese and add chopped olives and mushrooms.
Stir well and refrigerate overnight.
Stir again and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Mix well. Add flour, soda and salt; mix again.
Stir in chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 375° oven. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix with melted butter and 2 tablespoons powdered sugar.
Pat into oblong pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: hot rolls
directions: Heat milk to
scalding.
Add
tablespoons sugar, oil and salt.
Mix yeast with 4 tablespoons sugar.	Add warm water and stir until well
mixed.
When
milk is cooled to lukewarm, add eggs and yeast mixture.
Add flour, about 1 cup at a time. Beat with dough hoops
until you have added most of the flour. Use remainder of flour for kneading and knead well.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone and skin.
Chop coarsely.
Mix mushroom soup, chicken soup and sour cream in Bowl l. Add chopped chicken. Place chopped green onions in Bowl 2 Place grated cheese in Bowl 3 Put chicken broth, chili powder and oil in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Run each corn tortilla through boiling broth quickly.
Place on flat surface and add spoonful of soup/chicken mixture.
Add 1 tsp. green onion and 1 tsp. grated cheese.
Roll tortilla up and place in large pyrex dish.
Fill dish and add rest of ingredients on top.
Pour some of broth on also.
Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.
Add grated cheese on top and finish baking.

title: skillet pineapple upside down cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cornstarch.
Add 1/2 cup pineapple juice and cook over direct heat in heavy 10-inch skillet, stir constantly until sauce boils and becomes clear.
Add pineapple and butter. Drain cherries thoroughly and arrange in pattern in pineapple mixture.
Sift flour, measure and resift 3 times with salt and baking powder.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat the butter, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla 15 minutes. Spread over the graham crackers.
Dip the sliced bananas in pineapple juice.
Layer on and cover with drained pineapple, ending with Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill 8 hours to blend flavors, but may be eaten after chilling 1 hour.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Drain.
Add canned tomatoes and taco seasoning; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 can fried onions.
In bowl, mix cottage cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and eggs.
Place 3 tortillas on the bottom of a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Overlap 6 tortillas on sides of dish.
Spoon mixture evenly in dish.
Top with 3 teaspoons chips, then cheese mixture.
Bake, covered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Put onions on top and bake 5 minutes.
When serving, arrange tomatoes and lettuce around the edges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Sear
pork
chops
in
skillet.
Place
chops in baking dish. Drain sauerkraut and pour over chops.
Add 1 cup water. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Throw everything into ice cream freezer and crank!

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in 8 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch baking pan or dish.
Mix together onion soup mix, dressing and preserves.
Pour evenly over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: girdle buster cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pecans, 1 egg and melted margarine together and pour into bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Mix 10x sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs and coconut together and spread on top of other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, vanilla, milk, flour and baking powder.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold whites in mix last.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep in a well-sealed container.
Add 2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: spaghetti and shrimp platter
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to directions; drain.
In large skillet, heat butter and olive oil.
Add shrimp and garlic; cook until shrimp are opaque.
Combine hot, cooked spaghetti, shrimp mixture, Parmesan cheese, dill, salt and pepper; toss to mix.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown and season meat.
Place 6 of the torn tortillas in bottom of casserole.
Add drained brown meat, beans, onions, and add rest of tortillas.
Mix 2 cans chicken soup with Ro-Tel.
Pour over meat mixture.
Add cheese and bake.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients, onion and one half of the vinegar, place in blender, gradually add oil and rest of vinegar (important to keep from separating).
Then add celery seed and beat until thick. Makes 1 quart, keeps well.

title: avocado salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water until jello is dissolved; cool. Mash avocado and mix with mayonnaise and vinegar; mix into cooled jello.
Add crushed pineapple, whipped cream and walnuts.
Pour into serving bowl and chill.

title: tuna macaroni
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to box directions.
Add peas, carrots, tuna and cheese.
Mix well.

title: the best cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons of the vanilla for 10 minutes.
Butter a 9
x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour cream cheese mixture atop crumbs and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Mix together the sour cream and the 9 tablespoons sugar and the other 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Beat 10 minutes. Pour over cooled cream cheese mixture and refrigerate.
Fresh or frozen strawberries may be pushed lightly into sour cream topping when it's cool.

title: wanda's never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
In a bowl, mix water, egg and vinegar.
Mix all ingredients together. Work into a ball.
Roll out on floured board.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Saute pepper, onion and butter.
Add eggplant, tomatoes, salt and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining butter with bread cubes and spoon over eggplant.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until tender. Serves about 4.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl except corn flakes and butter.
Place mixed ingredients in large baking dish.
Mix butter and corn flakes in small bowl, then spread evenly over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano, add hamburger.	Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.

Put 1/2 of the spaghetti in a greased 9 X 13 pan.	Top with 1/2 vegetable mixture, sprinkle with 4 oz. cheese, repeat layers.	Mix the soup and water until smooth, pour over casserole.	Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake uncovered for 30-35 minutes at 350°.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Saute hamburger, onions and celery; add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Yields 50 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, onion soup mix and bread crumbs. Form into balls.
Simmer on top of stove chili sauce, water, brown sugar, kraut and cranberry sauce.
Mix until well blended.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fat-free rice pudding
directions: Bring 6 cups water to boil in large, heavy saucepan.
Add rice and boil, uncovered, 7 minutes.
Drain well.
Bring milk to boil in same saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally.
Add rice and salt.
Cook, uncovered, over medium-low heat, stirring often, until rice is very soft and absorbs most of the milk, about 15 minutes.
Rice should look creamy, not soupy and not dry.
When rice is cooked, stir in sugar.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in raisins and vanilla.
Serve warm, sprinkled with cinnamon.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: shells and vegetables salad
directions: Prepare shells and cheese as directed on package.
Toss shells and cheese with remaining ingredients.
Serve hot or chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Combine and set aside, flour, baking soda, and salt. Cream margarine and sugar. Add beaten egg and vanilla. Add flour mixture, blend well. Then add oatmeal, cheese, wheat germ and bacon. Mix well. Drop by rounded Tbsp. onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° about 16 minutes.

title: swiss fondue(original recipe from switzerland)
directions: May use 2 cups Gruyere cheese and 2 cups Emmenthaler cheese instead of Cheddar and Parmesan cheese, or 4 cups Swiss cheese.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Wash and drain cabbage.
Cut it up in chunks or slices.
Rid cabbage of water.
Add to the vegetable oil.
You may also use the bacon fat if you like.
Fry on medium heat, continually stirring the cabbage.
Add salt, pepper and sugar and cook for 10 to 15 minutes or to your desired texture.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add next 7 items and heat through.

title: lemon sheet cake
directions: Beat cake mix and eggs. Fold in pie filling. Spread in greased 15 x 10 x 1 pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes. Cool.

title: shrimp stew
directions: In a large saucepan over medium-high heat, heat the vegetable oil until hot.
Add onion and saute until translucent, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes and saute until softened, 2 to 3 minutes. Add shrimp and saute until opaque, about 3 minutes.
Stir in the Recaito.
Add the chicken stock, rice, asparagus tips, peas and olives.
Stir well and bring almost to a boil.
Serve at once. Makes 6 servings.

title: almond-crusted pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Generously grease loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Sprinkle 1/2 cup almonds over bottom and 2/3 up sides, pressing if necessary.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut up chicken in bite size pieces and place in casserole dish.
Mix broth, soup and Veg-All together and pour over chicken. Mix Bisquick and milk together and pour on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: barbecued sloppy joes
directions: Fry onion and hamburger in 4 tablespoons fat until it has lost its raw red color.
Stir until smooth and then add the other ingredients.
Simmer about 20 minutes and serve on hamburger buns.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in a 9 inch x 13 inch pan.
While cake is hot, punch holes in it with a fork.
Boil 2 cups sugar with 1 cup milk for 2 minutes.
Allow to cool.
Pour over cake.	Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Cover and refrigerate.
Better if it is allowed to set overnight.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: The day we brought this to the office, we ate so much we had to skip lunch!

title: st. patrick's day cupcakes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together (these do not need an electric mixer) first 6 ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine eggs, milk, oil and vanilla or almond extract.
Stir into flour just until combined. Fill greased or paper lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Frost with cream cheese icing; sprinkle with colored sugar and then milk chocolate pieces.
Makes 18.

title: jelly roll pancakes(makes eight 6-inch pancakes)
directions: In medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt. In small bowl or in blender, beat milk, eggs and oil. Stir egg mixture into flour mixture just until blended, a few lumps may remain. Heat greased or nonstick griddle or skillet over medium-high heat until a drop of water "dances" on the pan surface. Pour about 1/4 cup batter for each pancake. Cook until bubbles on top burst. Turn and cook on second side. Lift out with spatula and let cool slightly. Spread each pancake with about 2 teaspoons jam. Roll up and place on serving plate, seam side down. Keep warm in 250° oven. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: refried pinto beans
directions: Cook the beans.
When finished add the grease in an empty pan. Spoon out 2 cups of the beans.
Cook and stir, then add some bean juice.
Mash beans.
If beans seem a bit dry, add a little more juice.
Cut off burner and let simmer.
Cool.

title: easy quesadillas
directions: Mix sausage and beans together.
Spread over 2 tortillas, using half on each.
Sprinkle evenly with 3/4 cup cheese.
Drizzle with 1/4 C taco sauce.
Top with remaining tortillas.
Microwave 1 Quesadilla, covered with a paper towel, on a microwave-safe plate on high for 1 - 1 1/2 minutes.
Repeat with remaining Quesadilla.
Cut each into 8 wedges; serve with remaining 1/4 cup taco sauce, and remaining 1/2 cup cheese.

title: squash pickles
directions: Sterilize your jars and lids for 2 minutes; let cool, then add the following:
some dill weed, onion (1/4 wedges), jalapeno or chili pepper (1 or 2, depends on how hot you want it), garlic sections, sliced celery, sliced carrots, cucumbers and a dash of black pepper.

title: broccoli muffins
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Stir in corn muffin mix.
Use well-greased muffin tins or line with paper cups.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with mashed bananas.
Add nuts if desired.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 55 to 70 minutes.

title: apple plate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and allspice together.
Pour over apples in unbaked crust.
Pour 1/2 cup warm water over mixture and bake at 325° for 20 minutes, then place top crust on and bake until brown.

title: rosie's cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and spread out crackers.
Simmer melted butter and brown sugar for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour over the crackers.
Bake in a 400° oven for 5 minutes.

title: squash cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Boil water; add rice.
Remove from heat and let stand.
Fry bacon.
Keep 2 tablespoons of grease.
Brown pork chops in 1 tablespoon grease.
Mix eggs with 2 tablespoons of water.
In 1 tablespoon of grease, cook egg mixture until set.
Cut into narrow strips.
Stir in green onion, rice, soy sauce and bacon.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Place rice mixture with pork chops on top.
Brush with soy sauce.
Cook for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: lo-cal tomato juice dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until well blended.
Makes
1 cup.
Contains 25 calories per tablespoon.

title: my mama's coconut cream pies
directions: Put milk in heavy boiler and heat on low until warm-not hot. Beat egg yolks well and stir into milk.
Stir in corn starch mixture.
Turn heat up to medium cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in butter until it melts, add coconut and flavoring.
Put into pie shells.

title: honey nut cookies
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 2 minutes; then add vanilla, peanuts and peanut butter.
Stir in cornflakes.

title: butter crumshus coffee cake
directions: Cut together 1/4 cup butter, 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 cup brown sugar for topping and save.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Cut tomatoes and add all other ingredients.
Place in a medium size bowl.
Add olive oil and lime juice.
Stir ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 1 hour and serve with tortilla chips. Makes 2 cups.
Can be stored for up to a week.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger or turkey.
Combine sugar, milk, salt, chili powder, onion and garlic in bowl.
Blend well.
Add tomatoes, corn, black olives and corn meal.
Add browned meat.
Pour into a flat 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and allow to melt.

title: my favorite mushrooms
directions: Clean and remove mushroom stems.
Mince stems.
Snip parsley and mince.
Mince scallions and garlic.
Brush flat sides of mushroom caps with a little oil; place them in a low buttered baking dish.
Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add minced mushroom stems, parsley, scallions, salt, pepper and garlic; cook for about 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from stove.
Add enough bread crumbs to make a thick paste.
Stuff the mushroom caps; sprinkle the tops with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: teriyaki venison steak
directions: Mix soy sauce, brown sugar, ginger and oil. Make slits in meat and press in each slit the sliced garlic. Sprinkle steaks with Season All. Place steaks in marinade 5-6 hours or overnight in a covered dish in the refrigerator. Discard marinade and grill steaks until desired doneness.

title: chicken burritos
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil over medium heat until onion is translucent.
Add chicken; cook for 4 minutes or until no longer pink.
Stir in beans, 1/2 cup salsa and chili powder; cook 2 minutes longer.
Place tortillas between moist paper towels and microwave on high for 10 seconds.
Spoon 1/2 cup filling onto each tortilla; top with 1 tbsp. cheese.
Fold each into a burrito.
Serve with a cup of salsa, remaining cheese and sour cream.

title: orange-glazed pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in large shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally.
May be assembled ahead and allowed to marinate refrigerated.

title: shrimp omelet
directions: Saute shrimp, onion and bell pepper in butter or margarine. Add sauteed ingredients with eggs and cheeses.
Cook until done.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a hot, greased iron skillet. Bake at 425°.

title: apple-cranberry casserole(red)
directions: Spread apples in buttered baking dish. Spread cranberries on top of apples. Spread 2/3 cup sugar over apples and cranberries.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: With electric mixer, combine powdered sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and pour canned pie filling over the top.
Cover and place in refrigerator several hours until cool and firm.

title: chicken with mushroom gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coat chicken breasts with flour.
Melt butter and pour into a shallow baking dish.
Lay chicken breasts (skin side down) on top of melted butter and bake for 30 minutes. Turn chicken and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Pour off excess fat.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 15 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Add onion and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Marinate in refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix into large ball and eat on crackers.

title: apple berry sparkler
directions: Combine apple and cranberry juices, then chill.
Just before serving, stir in mineral water.
Serve over ice and garnish with lemon.

title: layered spanish dip
directions: Make this dip on a large enough serving dish so the layers are thin enough to dip.
Pizza pan works great.
Serves a large crowd. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Add and bake at 425° until brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, vegetable oil and eggs. Add vanilla. Mix in flour and spices. Add carrots and nuts. Place in greased and floured pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Prepare peaches and mix with 1 cup sugar.
Put butter in deep baking dish or pan and melt.
Stir up batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir. Put sugared peaches on top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Batter will rise to the top during baking and will brown and crisp.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening, then add cherries and nuts.
Combine liquid ingredients.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Stir only until flour is moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: harvest sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all the filling ingredients in a bowl, then beat until smooth. Pour into the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in an ungreased angel food or loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: "no bake" oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil, dill, salt and dressing in bowl.
Pour over crackers.
Store in Tupperware, shake frequently.
Store in cool place.

title: miniature ham pies
directions: Grease miniature muffin tins well.
Mix all ingredients and fill cups 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Drop by tablespoonful onto a hot griddle.
Fry slowly until browned on one side; turn and brown the other side.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Prepare Bundt pan by greasing well and dusting with granulated sugar.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, pudding mixes and hot water.
Add oil and eggs.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes until done.
Cool, then frost.

title: sausage bread
directions: Drain corn.
Brown sausage and crumble.
Mix all ingredients and place in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° in oven until done.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt butter, paraffin wax and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Lay out a sheet (long) of wax paper and coat with powdered sugar; roll into a log.
Chill and slice.
Can make several smaller rolls, chill then slice.

title: asparagus cheese strata
directions: In a saucepan, cover asparagus with water.
Cover and cook until just tender, but still firm.
Drain and set aside.
Lightly brush butter over one side of bread slices.
Place half of the bread, buttered side up, in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Layer with asparagus and ham. Cover with remaining bread, buttered side up.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake rolls in round pizza pan at 350° until golden brown, approximately 15 minutes; cool.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and onion; spread over cooled crust.
Spread vegetables on cheese mixture, slicing black olives around.
Sprinkle 2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese over all.
Serve cold.
Can use fruit in place of vegetables.

title: barbecues
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion.
Put all in a large electric roaster and simmer slowly.
Makes enough for 12 to 14 dozen buns.

title: kid's favorite hot dogs
directions: Cook hot dogs (grilled or in hot water) until done.
Place in buns; top with relish or chili sauce, diced green pepper, onion and tomato.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.

title: orange loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth, about 3 minutes. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. Punch holes in cake with wooden spoon handle.

title: chicken wings deluxe
directions: Wash chicken wings; cut off tips.
Mix soy sauce, brown sugar, mustard and garlic salt.
Marinate wings in sauce for 2 hours. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together hash browns, sour cream, soup, 1 stick melted magarine, cheese and onion.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Scrape carrots and cut into strips 1/4 inch thick and 1 1/2 inches long.
Place strips in a buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with brown sugar and butter. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Carrots may be sliced into thin slices instead of strips, if desired.
